product_title: Five-Column Graph Pocket Chart
review_headline: Crooked stitching, but otherwise a good product
review_body: I purchased this graph from Amazon recently.  They had the best price and it's exactly what I needed.  However, the slots are not all the same size.  I cut out cards with my kids names on them.  They fit fine everywhere until you get half way up the graph (specifically the fourth column) and the slots get smaller.  The stitching is angled, which is why this is happening.  Just by looking at the graph, you can see this.  That's disappointing.  Now I have to go back and cut down all the kids name cards.  Not a real difficult fix for me, but I would expect better from a Scholastic product.  I would suggest if you buy this product to look at it and make sure the name cards you cut out fit in all the spaces!

product_title: Epson Stylus Photo R2000 Wireless Wide-Format Color Inkjet Printer (C11CB35201)
review_body:
This printer does everything I want it to do. The ink consumption is very reasonable and the quality of the photographs are eye popping. There are things I would like to point out to people:
1. This is a photo printer not an "all-in-one"
2. There is a learning curve in working with a photo printer just as there is learning curve in editing photographs.
3. If you expect to use "bargain" photo paper you will be disappointed in the results.
4. If you are a photographer or graphic artist and would like control over the entire process this is a perfect printer for that process.
I also would say that I have experienced none of the problems that some people have complained about I feel most people who have issues are a result of inexperience in dealing with a high quality printer.

product_title: Canon Office and Business MX922 All in One Printer, Wireless and mobile printing
review_body:
I have not had any issues with this printer! I have ours totally on WiFi and have never hooked it to the PC. Another reviewer mentioned that you need to "manually" find your WiFi SSID and type out the password, so that is what I did as well. Apparently there may be an issue with WiFi WPS auto connect where It will not let you get connected to Google Cloud Print. I did NOT use this feature! There is a Google app called Canon Easy Photo Print (EPP) for your android that is just super simple and it works well, so Google Cloud print is almost not needed. Once it "attached" itself to my secure WiFi, all PC's, Android devices on the network recognized it, so super easy! Installed the program on main PC from the provided disc without any issues. I will say that I never had to read any instructions (which is amazing!) to get this thing "hooked" up to our network or to use the software! If you can read the LCD display window on the printer, make a few decisions and press a button a few times, insert a cd into your computer, read, make a few decisions, click a mouse a few times, you are golden!

First thing I printed was a picture off of my Galaxy S4 using the above mentioned APP. It was a lot quicker than our older Kodak ESP7 and the picture looked very nice printed on Canon GlossyII paper. Next was the auto document feader (ADF) to scan to the PC. Scanning is very important to us as most every important document ends up in one our our RAID drives. From the PC software you have a bunch of choices for scanning which is super nice, good job Canon! I loaded documents into the ADF, went to the PC, chose both sided (duplex) scan, chose a RAID drive as a destination, selected a quality, B&W / Color, etc. Then start. It did take a while for the duplex part to shuffle it around, but a huge improvement over our old ESP7 which was manual load every page. Now I could chase kids around, goof around, drink some coffee, enjoy life a bit more! Scan complete, everything ended up super clear, sharp, pages in order with little effort on my part. If you operate a busy office and expect to have fast production in scanning or copying, then this printer is NOT for you. If you have a bit more relaxed schedule like mine for home use it is great.

We turn our printer completely off after each use, so it does take about 30 seconds or so to "warm up." All copies and print outs look really good and are printed in a reasonable time. We use the cheapest paper we can find and everything looks really nice! I suspect the quality would be better with a better quality paper? It is not laser printer fast, nor dot matrix line printer slow, again if you are running production and looking for speed, this is NOT for you! It does need to do the typical ink jet printer cycling thingy which is on average with other ink jets I have used, faster than most older printers including our old ESP7, I suspect slower that some more $$$ units?

The only gripe I have is pretty small potato's! When you scan it will save it to a .pdf file which is good, but you cannot crop and or adjust it before it is saved. Kodak software allowed you to see the image, make adjustments, crop size, THEN save all the changes into the final scan. Canon could make a software / firmware update for this!

We have no use for the FAX so I cannot review this! I will mention that I am more comfortable using computer software, I have built our main PC from the ground up, so if you don't have a clue about these things, it may not go as smooth for you. I would recommend asking that geek friend of yours to lend a helping hand, but once set up, it will be very easy to maintain and use.

PROS:
Decent (average) price for this unit. If you can read, you can use it! Individual ink cartridges are reasonable priced and easy to replace. Holds lots of paper & photo paper. WiFi means you can place it anywhere, including a closet, just need power! Easily print pictures from your smart phone via WiFi. ADF means no more manually loading papers for scan/copy. Duplex ADF and print. Can print on printable CD's. Software gives you many many choices for all functions! There is a "Quiet Time" setting from within the software to cut back on noise during sleepy times.

CONS:
Not enough speed for high production office settings. You cannot get firmware updates via WiFi, Canon, you need to fix this! Software could have minor tweaks. Unit is on the bigger side, could be slimmed down a bit.

I highly recommend this printer for light to medium home use, it has proven to be a good investment for our family!ower! Easily print pictures from your smart phone via WiFi. ADF means no more manually loading papers for scan/copy. Duplex ADF and print. Can print on printable CD's. Software gives you many many choices for all functions! There is a "Quiet Time" setting from within the software to cut back on noise during sleepy times.

CONS:
Not enough speed for high production office settings. You cannot get firmware updates via WiFi, Canon, you need to fix this! Software could have minor tweaks. Unit is on the bigger side, could be slimmed down a bit.

I highly recommend this printer for light to medium home use, it has proven to be a good investment for our family!

review_headline: Bright and Colorful, Fun and Easy to Use
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:59e2140bb3046008399da0c5558772a9]] I like to decorate things and work on crafts with my family. I try to keep a variety of pencils, crayons, and markers around the house for when we decide to get crafty together. What I didn't have until recently were these Colore chalk markers.
This particular set comes with a nice little variety of very bright colors and a soft, but sturdy silicone marker holder.
These markers are extremely vibrant and I love that you can write on glass, binders, plastic, and a ton of different surfaces. They take a minute or two when you first get them to finally get the ink out, but once you do, it's super simple to use them.
These are perfect to use to write messages on car windows, your business windows, boards, mirrors, and more.
My son has a blast using these and says he loves all of the colors.
Great quality too. We're very happy with these.

I received this set of Colore' Chalk Markers for reviewing purposes. All opinions stated here are based solely off of my own experience with the product. No other compensation was received.

product_title: Ritron RQX-451-XT UHF Callbox
review_body:
The Ritron Callbox does look like a good product. Unfortunately the product description is totally incomplete.
Before I want to place an order, I would like to have answers to the following questions:
a) What is the difference between the different models offered, such as:
Ritron RQX-151-XT, Ritron RQX-156-XT, or Ritron RQX-457-XT?
b) What is different about the Ritron RGG1-156-XT-KP VHF that makes it twice as expensive?
c) What accessories are included with a specific model, such as base station and/or mobile communicator and gate activating relay?
d) Do this model base station and/or mobile controller come with a charger that is powered by 120 VAC?
d) Can the callbox that is at the gate be powered by 12 VDC?
e) Most important: Does this model callbox come with relay contacts that can be remotely activated to open the gate?

product_title: Abdtech 130" Mini LED Projector 800 Lumens Multimedia Beamer Portable Home Theatre Projectors
review_headline: This thing is AMAZING - I am so happy with it
review_body:
This thing is AMAZING - I am so happy with it. Not only did I order it yesterday and receive it today (thank you Amazon Prime!), but it is so easy to use and perfect for my needs. Out of the box, plugged in and connected to my laptop - choose usb or hdmi and you're ready to project! I'm not sure if the people who couldn't get it focused just weren't patient but it was pretty easy to get the image focused for me.

The attached images are projected onto textured oilcloth, too, so not even a smooth surface. And the images are pretty clear! Definitely perfect for outdoor movie night! And when I tested it with chromecast it was in my bedroom and the wall was perfect for the projection. The images would probably be even crisper with a screen.

The only negative I can think of is that the sound is low so you need nice speakers. Even with my desktop USB speakers it isn't quite loud enough. Problem solved wih nicer speakers though. Otherwise the image quality is excellent, the thing is SO easy to use. These images are with my laptop and HDMI outside. Works easily with chromecast as well.

Overall - don't hesitate and just order this! You won't regret it.

product_title: EPS Replacement Toner Cartridge HP 131A for Hp Laserjet Pro M251 M276
review_body: So far so good.  I have used only one color, but my HP Color Laser Printer M 250 accepted it with only one "Not an HP Product" notice on the status panel.  I tapped "OK" and it said "Ready". The material status panel reports the percentage available for all 4 colors. The color quality of the printouts remains excellent.  My previous HP Color Printer 2600N, punished me for using non HP cartridges by requiring me to press a check button for each non HP color, every time I turned the printer on. then failed to show the availability status of each non HP color, forcing me to guess when the toner was running out by periodically pausing and examining the printouts for fading.

product_title: Valuetoner Remanufactured Ink Cartridge Replacement for New Generation Hewlett Packard HP 564XL (4 Black, 2 Cyan, 2 Magenta, 2 Yellow, 2 Photo Black)
review_headline: This product was rated at 4 stars and the price was great, so I bought it
review_body: I have bought several refurbished print cartridges and used them with no problems and I didn't think twice about buying them on Amazon.  No matter the price I use the buyer recommendations to make my purchase.  This product was rated at 4 stars and the price was great, so I bought it.  What a nightmare.  When I opened one of the color cartridges and removed the nozzle cap, ink started to leak out on my hands.  I assumed the cartridge was defective and I resealed it.  I then tried the black cartridge. When I open the cartridge it did not leak, so I assumed it was OK. When I turned the cartridge over to install it into the print head slot a large amount ink poured out into the print head slot and interior of the printer. I did my best to get all of the ink out of the print head and printer. After cleanup I reinstalled my old cartridge (which still had some ink in it) and ran a print test, the color work, but no black print.  I tried 4 or 5 head cleaning cycles and still nothing.  I then went to Office Max and got a "new" genuine HP cartridge.  After Installing it I tried several print cycles and test, but again no black characters. I assume the printer head is clogged with ink and would have to be opened, the head removed for cleaning or a new print head.  In either case I found the same printer (HP6525) online for $108, which I will but instead of paying to have this one repaired.  I wouldn't give this product a 1/2 star

review_headline: Didn't last half as long as original cartridges!
review_body:
Genuine Canon ink? I find that kind of hard to believe. These were my first set of replacement cartridges for my Pixma Pro 100. Previously, I had been using the ink that came packaged with the printer. That ink lasted me about 5-6 months doing a moderate amount of photo printing. I've done less than half of my previous prints and the black ink has already run out as well as one of the magentas The light cyan is also low. I also purchased the grey cartridge through Amazon and it is 3/4 of the way down as well.

The packaging looked legit as well as the cartridges themselves, but I find it awfully odd that this set of cartridges don't match up to the shelf life of the set packaged with the printer. I will be buying directly through Canon from now on. Buyer beware!

product_title: HP Prime Graphing Calculator
review_body:
I'm an old hp48 user from the 90's, This calculator has resparked my love for the HP. I got the hp50g to replace my failing hp480 but it was just a clunky lame refresh. The HP Prime is to me as the first day I opened my HP48, a new world of experimentation. I don't use it for school stuff just work and my hobbies, so I can't comment on CAS stuff or VS TI. HPPL Rocks, and it's RPL implementation is solid. HP Should put a phone in it and call it a day as I'd rather use this beast than my phone as the keys are bliss. Battery life is golden too.
Cons.
HP included a Hard TI style case!!! Yuck, give me a fabric case with a zipper.
I/O: This is made for testing so there is zero external communications such as user programmable Serial, beeps or even activating the lights. HP 48 let you get at it all.
Lowlevel instructions: again since it's made for testing HP removed anything to give you access to the raw platform

review_body: Beware that this printer is able to handle AirPrint from wireless devices such as iPad & iPhone but is not wireless cabs capable. It took awhile to setup the AirPrint function with both my wireless devices. The setup directions included with this printer are very sketchy on the AirPrint setup and the telephone support wasn't very help either. After poking around the Brother website for awhile, I discovered a Brother print app is required for printing from an iPad ( not mentioned in the setup directions) after installing the app, I was able print from my iPad with no trouble at all. Printer works great and printing is a snap from either my iPad or iPhone. If you buy this printer, save yourself some aggravation and immediately go to the App Store and download the Brother print app. Just wish Brother's tech support was more knowledgable about Airprinting.

product_title: VTech LS6475-3 DECT 6.0 Expandable Cordless Phone with Answering System and DECT Cordless Headset, Silver with 2 Handsets and 1 Headset
review_headline: ... cordless headset for the cordless phone set is a great idea. I do wish there was an option ...
review_body:
The cordless headset for the cordless phone set is a great idea. I do wish there was an option to pair a bluetooth headset with my cordless phone. I'm not talking about pairing my cell phone with my cordless phone, but pairing my small, comfortable to use bluetooth headset (originally made for use with cell phones) with my cordless phone handset. It just makes sense.

Short of that, VTech needs to re-design the cordless headsets that they make for the DECT 6.0 phones. The ear piece is flimsy and breaks easily. We have had 2 now and both have broken off at the attachement/hinge where the ear hook attaches to the headset. It needs to be made out of better material, be easily replaceable, or just completely redesigned.

Overall we have had the phones for a few years and they work pretty well and are used non-stop. The speakerphone feature on one headset has stopped working and the earpiece on the headset sucks.

product_title: Displays2go Wire Display Rack for Books, Magazines and CDs, 29-Inch Wide Floor-Standing Fixture with 10 Display Tiers, Black (WRF10T29)
review_body:
I was a little wary after reading the reviews, but decided to give this a chance. It's sturdier than I expected. I'm not saying you could load this thing up with textbooks or other especially heavy / over-sized volumes, but it held up adequately when I tested it with trade paperbacks. I haven't actually used it (other than setting it up to test) though, so if it turns out to be less sturdy than it seems, I'll update my review.

Set-up is extremely easy -- and by 'extremely easy', I mean non-existent. You take it out of the box, pop out the back support, and that's it.

The reason I'm giving this 4 stars instead of 5 is because it scratched me when I was removing it from the box, and I still have a small wound. . The manufacturer should round out or otherwise modify the wire ends so they don't snag skin.

EDIT: I've used this several times now and it has held up nicely. No complaints.

product_title: Dell B1265dfw Laser Multifunction Wireless All-in-One Printer - Fax/Scan/Copy/Print - Monochrome
review_headline: Do not buy under any circumstances.
review_body:
Wow is this thing awful. We ordered one for our office and it's been a giant headache the whole time.

Scanning is a nightmare. Maybe if you just had this thing plugged into one PC it wouldn't be so bad. But Dell Printer Manager software is beyond garbage when running from the server. Aside from not saving settings properly, you cannot delete printers from the delete printers menu. It just doesn't allow you to do the things it says it can do. Oh! And you can't even uninstall the software properly since there is no uninstaller package. This software is poorly written and borderline DANGEROUS for your network if you install it on a server.

The worst part is you can't even use some of the features without that software. Want to scan to a shared drive? Use Dell Printer Manager! Want to update the firmware? Use Dell Printer Manager! Want do do anything? Use Dell Printer Manager! Too bad the software breaks literally EVERY feature on the printer. The software basically locks up if you try to run it more than once and you have to power cycle the printer to get it to respond to anything. But even that doesn't work anymore and I'm entirely unable to scan because it wants me to USE DELL PRINTER MANAGER.

Seriously, avoid this printer and this garbage software at all costs. Dell sent me a replacement and it's been an even worse headache. I'd outright return it if they'd bother replying to my emails.

product_title: Sentinel High Security Micro-Cut Paper/Credit Card Shredder
review_headline: Easy Setup, great shredding power, cheap feeling
review_body:
For shredding power and quality of shred, this would be five stars. Unfortunately, the cheap plastic housing that will inevitably break, and feels quite flimsy for this price level, knocks it down one star.

Pros:
- Nice small dice shredding. Better than all comparable price models I have tested.
- Handles credit cards, multiple sheets, staples all with easy. No blocking or jamming up.
- Easy to tell when on and off due to a bright light, and little concern that it will be left on for little ones to get into.

Cons:
- Cheap feeling housing. It's very thin plastic that doesn't feel it will stand the test of time. Like a $5 trash can feeling.
- The casters are so tiny. Almost pointless, really.

product_title: HI-VISION 6 Pack Compatible PGI-225 CLI-226 Ink Cartridge Replacement (Large Black,Black,Cyan,Yellow,Magenta,Gray) for PIXMA iP4820,iX6520,MG5320,MG5120,MG6120 Wireless,MG8120,MX892
review_body:
Love the reviews, like "not genuine Canon ink", really? Then there's the ones that cry "ink sprayed all over my hands, the cat and dripped on floor". But agree that the color is not quite as good as genuine ink but close enough for general printing and looks as good as drugstore printing. You want it better then pony up the $75 for a full set of genuine ink. I'm on my 4th set of tanks so $28 vs $300!

Place new tank in disposable paper towel, pull off top plastic seal, which now lets the tank equalizes with room pressure. Now twist off bottom plastic cap/plug and immediately snap into carriage with out squeezing tank in any way on the sides. Since using many third party ink tanks with IP4000 and newer printers, I have never had ink gush out but there is always the chance of mis-manufactured tanks. Plan ahead without white cat or rugs, no?

product_title: Dell Computer B1160w Wireless Monochrome Printer
review_headline: I couldn't get it to work at all
review_body:
Using WPS, I was able to get the printer to recognize my network, but it kept assigning itself a 169.* IP address, and refused to use DHCP, which meant it couldn't access the network.

I tried to use the manufacturer-supplied printer manager software to connect to it, in the hopes of being able to manually set a static IP, but on my computer (a Mac running 10.10 Yosemite) the software could not locate the printer.

So, there's nothing I could do to make it work. Returned.

product_title: HP Photosmart 7525 e-All-in-One Inkjet Printer: 4.3" Touch Screen , Wireless, Duplex Print, Copy, Scan, Fax
review_headline: Good for small office or home office
review_body: Great little small office or home office printer. My wife and I bought one a few years ago when this model was still new-ish. I have since purchased several for construction project trailers so our field supervisors have the ability to print, scan and copy both B&W and color documents. The Wireless Direct feature is quite nice so they don't have to have wi-fi on the job to print from their iPads directly to the printer. Also, being able to scan to email, to flash drive, and to a computer are nice. The photographs it prints (depending on settings, camera, paper, etc.) are not the best I've seen but definitely worthy of a frame. If you need some flexible options but don't use a printer/copier/scanner daily, this is not a bad choice for the money. I have yet to be disappointed with the 2 that I purchased.

product_title: Pentel EnerGel Alloy RT Premium Liquid Gel Pen, 0.7mm
review_headline: From one pen snob to another, this one is the best I've found.  Writes better than Lamy or Monte-Blank depending on paper used.
review_body:
I've spent $70 and $80 on other pens, but this cheaper pen writes a lot better and more dependably, and the refills are cheaper too! Great weight and decent quality for the cost. The pen itself is not made to the standards I'd like, but nothing else writes as well... most roller ball pens stop writing very well after much contact on credit card receipts, post-it notes and other waxy papers... this one will write on waxed papers and keep writing well until it is out of ink. With almost 100% crystal ball accuracy I can tell my pen is out of ink when it stops performing flawlessly. I've had better luck with the refills purchased at staples for some reason (newer maybe), and if your climate is excessively hot you may want to go with the fine tip to prevent leaking.

I'm a huge pen snob... this is the one I've settled on. If I could find a better pen for $200 I would buy it, but I don't think it's out there. The clips on these do occasionally break, and the threads do occasionally strip out.. one of these pens typically lasts me about 4 months probably, but pretty good considering how often I use it every day.

product_title: KANSANG Magnetic Brown Retro Vintage Ancient Old Book Bible Pattern Style PU Leather Stand Smart Case for Apple iPad Air 5 Generation Retina with 1xScreen Protector and 1x Stylus Pen(and NOT for iPad Air 2), iPad Air 2 available now, please check our store
review_body:
Pros:
- iPad in case looks great when completely closed. Looks like a real book.

- comes with a (cheap but working) stylus

Cons:

- iPad slides around while inside the case. Thus, the camera is not properly aligned with the opening of the case, the iPad screen is partially covered by one of the borders and the home button is also partially covered, and the front camera is also covered.

- sleep / wake function does not work with iPad Air 1st Gen.

- strong odor from the case; not sure what chemical it is but it irritates the lungs and the eyes.

- material is cheaply made: some stitching inside case is coming loose upon delivery of package,

- iPad slides out of position inside case when placed in landscape mode / position. The iPad gets stuck under one of the borders every time I try to use the landscape mode /position.

Overall, I give this case 2.75 stars only for looks. The fitting is designed terribly, the material is very cheap, and the sleep / wake function does not work as described by seller.

product_title: Dual Monitor Mount LCD arm,Full Motion Desk mounts for 10"-27" Computer Monitor, /w Gas Spring Monitor arm and Clamp or Grommet Desktop Support
review_headline: Dual monitor blues; cured by Fleximounts
review_body: My desk is the most annoying thing I have ever had this dis-pleasure of working on (a symptom of receiving a hand me down from my brother 5 years ago). The desk has almost no surface area so as you can imagine, having two monitors on it as well as a keyboard and notebook is absolutely a nightmare. Further to that, the top of my desk is only a few feet from the floor, so when I sit at my desk, I am slouching to meet my monitor pixel-to-eye. Seeing as how I am not set to inherit my brother's current desk for another couple of years and I can't be bothered to buy my own, I decided that my back health is actually quite important to me and I took to the internet in search of a solution that didn't involve stacking encyclopedias under my monitors in an attempt to raise them to eye level. Enter, the Fleximounts Full Motion Dual Arm Desk Mounted Spring Arm (What a name!). I had the good fortune to get this wonder 50% off and I was overjoyed that I did. Gone are my troubles of desk space maintenance. I neglected to take a photo of it, but my beloved notebook is off-camera, basking in the glorious space that the Fleximounts arm has provided it. I've also been spared a visit to the chiropractor because I can now adjust the height and position of my monitors. I record voice-overs, so its great to be able to pivot the monitors to point up at me while I read lines off of them. I couldn't ask for a better mount for my monitors, so thank you VERY MUCH, Fleximounts!

product_title: FLEXIMOUNTS Universal Stable Portable Stand for Tablets E-readers and Smartphones, Durable Body, Compatible for Apple iPads iPad Air, iPad Mini / New iPad Mini, iPhone 6 5S 5C 5 4S 4; Samsung Galaxy Tab 2 Tab 3 Tab 4 , Note 8.0 10.1, S5, S4, S3, S2,Galaxy S4 S5; Google Nexus 4,7,10; Asus EeePad Transformer, New HTC One (M8),Lenovo Tab
review_headline: This Fleximount Stand is exactly what I was looking for, lightweight and convenient.
review_body: A couple months ago I finally gave into buying a tablet, I have used a laptop for years but finally got tired of how much space it takes up.  Having a tablet in my travel bag has been extremely convenient because I fly regularly, the long flights are quite boring without something to watch.  The only downside of my tablet is it does not have a stand to prop it up and free me from holding it.  Prior to my most recent flight my friend kindly got me a fleximount stand as a thank you for the work I had completed.  My first impression of the stand was that it was well built, compact, light, and easy to carry.  I used it during my twelve hour flight home and loved every minute of it.  The stand held my tablet at the perfect angle to allow me to lay back and relax.  This stand has certainly earned a spot in my travel bag, it relieves the frustration of holding a tablet and is still small enough that it is really easy to carry along with me.  Thank you for the awesome product, I will likely be getting another in the future to pass onto my brother.

review_body: Canon products I have (including a few Canon high end cameras, Canon fax & this printer) are alway beautifully made and technically excellent. The one major recommendation I have is the need for a higher capacity toner cartridge. 2 after-market toners have only lasted 1 month each for average use in a medical office. I may try a Canon genuine toner next & check its longevity and then try a different after-market toner company (the ones I have used are probably from EPS).  This machine has excellent print quality, speed, ease of use, quiet & relatively small foot print.  It operates seamlessly in Mac OS (now Mavericks and the prior OS; I intend to install Yosemite soon). It's largely plastic but appears very sturdy. Easy to remove & place replaceable elements. Gives good warnings of low toner. Looks good too.

product_title: Quartet Infinity Glass Marker Board,
review_headline: Very nice whiteboard, but terrible for magnets
review_body:
As a whiteboard, this is very nice. It's well made, it looks great, and the glass surface works well for writing and cleanup. If you're looking for a good "premium" whiteboard, you'll likely be satisfied.

However, as other reviewers have noted, it's advertised as a magnetic board, and it's quite bad at the magnetic part. The glass is thick enough that magnets have a hard time sticking to the metal plate behind the glass. Even the "heavy duty" magnets I purchased on Amazon that claim to be 3x stronger than traditional whiteboard magnets (and indeed are quite strong) didn't stick enough to hold up a piece of paper. We ended up returning this item because we need to be able to use magnets to hang papers.

product_title: Five Star Advance Student Weekly / Monthly Planner
review_headline: Not Only Perfect for Backpacks, It's Great for Purses too ...
review_body:
I always have a calendar nearby to keep track of various things. I not only try to keep track of the boys' schedule, or when my husband has to work overtime, I use it to keep track of medical appointments, what I fixed for dinner (sounds tedious but it sure comes in handy when someone complains that I haven't fixed their favorite meals in a really long time, when I did fix it last month.) and anything that I can think of to keep track of.

The daily part is big enough to jot down notes and reminders. The nicest thing about this the monthly view, which comes in handy for me. I have a dry erase board that I have for everyone else to keep track of their schedules and I can use this planner to keep track of events months before the date.

I think the pencil holder is a nice addition. I will put my pens there instead and certain business cards to keep track of instead of littering my fridge.

This is a nice planner. It fits in my purse easily. It also fits in my desk as well. It is bright enough that if I have to ask my boys to get me my planner, they know exactly what they are looking for.

If I was a student, this would definitely be handy to have. It's really good for all ages.

product_title: Wolverine F2D Super 20MP 4-In-1 Film to Digital Converter, Convert 35mm, 126, 110 and Super 8 into digital in seconds.
review_headline: Fast, easy way to view and transform negatives and slides into a digital format
review_body:
I have always used a scanner to digitize prints of my old photos, but the negatives have been lost in a time warp. I still have them, but I had no easy way to see what they were photos of - until I discovered the Wolverine Converter.

I used the converter on 35mm and 110 negatives. (It also will convert slides and capture frames from Super 8.) I have spent more time than I expected sifting through envelopes full of old negatives and revisiting family, friends, places, and events from the past.

NOT OVERLY TECHNICAL. The device is straightforward to use and not high tech. There is a small screen for selecting options (film type, convert and save, upload, etc.) and for viewing the image. Initially, I found it a little clunky to use - it requires pushing buttons and scrolling through screen options - but was simple once I got accustomed to it.

VERSATILE. I connected the converter to my pc, saved the images directly on the converter, and then uploaded them to the computer. Alternatively, the converter comes with an adapter that can be plugged into the wall, and images can be saved to an SD card for printing or upload - so a computer is not necessary. The unit does allow some color adjustment for RGB, but I found it easier to use my photo editing software after uploading to make any corrections.

GOOD QUALITY, LARGE IMAGE SIZE. Image are digitized into jpg files at 5472 x 3648 pixels and average about 2.5mb each. The detail was very good, even on my older negatives, some which were 50 years old. Something to be aware of: if there is dust on the negatives, it will scan right along with the image, so clean film and a dust-free area is important. A cleaning brush is included with the unit, which helps.

The Wolverine Converter is a fast, uncomplicated way to view and transform negatives and slides into a digital format. It is a lightweight, compact unit that is simple to use, takes up little space, and is easy to store.

product_title: HI-VISION 2 PK Remanufactured HP 61XL CH563WN CH564WN,NEW CHIP HY Black+Tri-Color Ink Cartridge Replacement for Deskjet 1010,2540 All-in-One,Envy 4500 e-All-in-One,5530 e,Officejet 4630 e-All-in-One
review_headline: HI-VISION HI-YIELDS ink cartridges overcome HP priinter's resistance.
review_body:
After initial resistance by my HP Officejet 4530, things settled down except for an occasional false "out of ink" warning. After I closed the warning, everything continued to work properly. Output quality is very good, though the printer has an odd quirk of printing a solid black band where the on-screen image is a row of column captions. That also happens with original HP ink cartridges, so I do not blame the Hi-Vision versions.
I have only used these cartridges for about three weeks, and I do not believe I am even close to their advertised capacity. At the beginning, the HP printer tried to reject the cartridges by pointing out that they were not original HP, but after rejecting the pop-up objections from HP, the new ink cartridges continued to do a nice job. Always buy the XL cartridges with high yield and extra ink. The basic HP cartridges that came with the printer were a joke, running out of ink after 2 or 3 dozen pages. These are continuing to run well so I really don't know how long they will keep up the excellent work. So far, so good.
I will buy them again.

product_title: Canon Pixma MG2922 Inkjet Printer
review_headline: For IoS devices, you really need Air Print
review_body:
I bought this because I needed an all in one that day to scan some documents and the store was out of the Air Print model.

It is not a good choice for IoS devices and can only print pictures, not documents or webpages from those devices. The set up was easy for the PC but not for the Ipad or Iphone. Their app is not user friendly at all.

Other than the problems with IoS devices, it prints and does the job for a cheap price. I'm not sure I've ever heard a printer be so loud printing. There is also a pretty decent delay between loading the paper and printing which makes me wonder if it's going to work or not.

In the future I will be sure to get Air Print for ease of use with our devices.

Update; If I could give this zero stars I would. My unit broke after about 2 months. I find the Customer Service at Canon to be one of the worst I've ever encountered. They did send me a new one but couldn't manage to track their own prepaid return label. I got it set up... painfully AGAIN. A few weeks later, I changed my router and upgraded to Windows 10. Having had one experience with customer service I waited a few weeks to call because Windows 10 was quite new and frankly I didn't want to deal with them. After about 90 minutes the rep managed to get 1 out of 4 needed devices to print IF I connected the printer cable. Then he told me I could figure out the rest on my own. At that point I didn't protest because I didn't really want to be on the phone even longer. Needless to say I will never buy another Canon again. They used to make quality products, but not anymore.

review_body: I purchased these pens at Target for about the same price they are listed for here. I love these pens and now have something to compare them to because I also purchased the Fiskars 48-pen set after hearing good reviews on those. Personally, I like the Write Dudes better and they are less expensive. These pens write smooth, the color is vibrant and they last a LONG time. After one coloring page with my Fiskars (that was about the same amount of space to color as I've used these for), two of my Fiskars were nearly out of ink already. First time using them. The Write Dudes pens also seem to be made better than the Fiskars - feel a bit sturdier in the hand. I've colored many mandalas and patterns with the Write Dudes and all of the pens still have a good amount of ink. The ink does take a few minutes to dry after applying, so be careful about that. I would highly recommend these pens, even over some of the more expensive brands. When it's time to replace, I will buy another set of these.

product_title: Epson T223XL120 DURABrite Ultra High-Capacity Black Ink Cartridge
review_headline: Great cartridge for a great Epson printer!
review_body:
It's really nice to have a black only ink jet printer that has a long lasting black cartridge. This prints up to 2400 pages (at 5% coverage which is a page of double-spaced type). We had an inkjet before this in the same situation that was color and that gave us much less prints per cartridge. With these cartridges and the Epson WorkForce WF-M1030 printer we save a lot over our other options.

While there are other inkjet printers that have 2400 page cartridges for less than $50, they're color inkjet. Even if you don't print the color you still get forced to change the color cartridges after a while (or your color printheads get ruined). There is an even worse problem--when the color thinks it's out of a color, it won't even print black! So only having to deal with one cartridge and not needing to buy color definitely makes it worth the fact that the cartridge is more expensive than some.

And it's cheaper than some too. $50 divided by 2400 pages is two cents a page. There are no other consumables to buy so that's cheap.

It looks like Epson isn't going to put out another inkjet, so I'm going to have to find another solution someday. But for now, I'm going to use this as long as I can!

product_title: TruBind Comb Binding Machine (TB-C20A)
review_body:
After reviewing small craft binders, I decided to just pay twice to nearly three times the smaller crafty sizes and go with this full size machine (price nearly half original). I don't have space issues.
I ordered 2-9-15 from a web store and UPS delivered 2-13-15. I was binding printed pages of an e-book within minutes. Then I carefully tore off the paperback bindings of two sewing books, trimmed the cover and/or pages (glue) with scissors or http://www.amazon.com/Fiskars-Titanium-Paper-Trimmer/dp/B003Z3FSJ2/ref=sr_1_15?ie=UTF8&qid=1423882029&sr=8-15&keywords=fiskars+rotary+paper+trimmer and bound those. The books required the combs to be trimmed to length with scissors I've dedicated to paper and crafts. The excess combs are still long enough to become little notepads.
Choice of three margin depths...how far from the paper edge to punch the holes. I should have tested the depths first, but afterwards punched the instruction leaflet for a sampler and laminated it for durability. http://www.amazon.com/Purple-Cows-Laminator-Assorted-3016c/dp/B005FVNH68/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1423887039&sr=8-1&keywords=purple+cow+laminator My laminator was purchased from our local Costco.
Be sure to keep the pages in order and punch the same direction, otherwise you may need to trim top or bottom page margins to fit. One book was a bit of a boo boo, but nothing to make myself upset over, because now it lays flat; the goal.
It has no limit to paper length (removable and adjustable edge guide) and you can bind thick books/manuals up to two inches thick (largest comb size). It has dies/cutting pins you can disengage (take out of service) which I did to punch the small sewing books.
I also purchased three sizes of clear combs (the amount of paper they hold) of 100 count each size. Although, there are many colors to choose from. Pennies to replace if damaged.
I own a few hardbound hobby books with comb bound pages within. This appears simple enough to copy to my many beautifully hardbound hobby books to keep the integrity of the binding, but have a lay flat book and pages. It will require trimming the inner or outside margins of pages to fit inside the hard cover. I don't believe (or want to test) this will cut through a hard cover.
Binding pages of topics/hobby instructions that are currently stored one or two pages to a page protector in 3 ring binders will now require only 1/3 to 1/4 the space and weight; and be easier to physically handle. And retain the option to remove or add pages.
Two year warranty. I am already a happy binder/rebinder and will be teaching our preschool to preteen grandsons to use this, too. With my permission and supervision. It's that simple.
I did not buy this from Amazon, though the reduced price was the same. The bulk buy of combs at the web store made the sale, and $4.95 shipping/no tax. Overall less than Amazon Prime with tax.
EDIT: 4-22-15 Those purchased craft books are wire bound. Still I'll be taking some of my craft books apart, comb binding them and reinserting/glueing the comb bound pages back into the hard cover. NOTE: wire bound is not spiral bound.py to my many beautifully hardbound hobby books to keep the integrity of the binding, but have a lay flat book and pages. product_title: School Smart Heavyweight Ruled Index Cards - 5 x 8 inches - Pack of 100 - White
review_body: There used to be an industry standard for index cards.  Index-weight paper was usually 110 lbs.  The cards made from this kind of heavy paper was thick, like an index card should be.  Now, too many companies are making what they call 'index cards' on much thinner paper.  I bought a pack of these so-called 'index cards' made by School Smart because they were called 'heavyweight'.  They're not.  They are about the thickness of 3 sheets of copy paper, probably printed on 60 lb. paper.  As a result, they aren't cards at all.  I would never buy this product again and feel cheated.

product_title: Scotch Thermal Laminator, 2 Roller System, Fast Warm-up, Quick Laminating Speed (TL901C-T)
review_headline: Small and fast to heat up!
review_body: I'll start with the only con I could see: the smell. It smells like burning plastic when it's laminating. But this is the first hot laminator I have ever owned (I owned cold ones in the past that rolled the item through two plastic sheets), and it's perfect for my needs.  I like that it's small. It takes up very little space. So when you are not using it, it fits perfectly in a drawer out of sight.  It heats up fast. It was less than 5 minutes from when I turned it on. The "ready" light turned from white to green when it was ready.  I laminated a few small items in the sheets, because I hate wasting, and I was able to cut around them and not have them come apart. One of the things was even slightly thicker (needed the 5 mil setting) and it came out really good.  Overall, happy with this item.

Called HP Customer service - 68 minutes later they are sending a new printer. Resolution so far is OK, we'll see what happens. HP Service while good in the end was slow and tedious process, numerous transfers, holds with no on hold music which is always confusing. Ultimately the last two service reps were good. But, I've wased an hour of my Saturday....

I buy HP products just so this won't happen. HP like many US comapnys (Maytag comes to mind) that used to stand for quality have decided to comptee with the low price, low quality competitors. I.E. Brother and Whirlpool, only to leave consumers dissapointed. I suspect along the path executives from these companies had great pay days and personally succeeded, but ruined quality brands that once stood for something.

product_title: Nouvelles Images Vintage Sheet Music - 2015 Calendar (YC 029)
review_headline: A Year od Lost Music to Ponder.
review_body:
This Calendar was a glimpse into the past of many of those songs that our grandparents and great grandparents sang around the piano on the Sunday night family get togethers. Unfortunately for us most pieces are no longer available, with the possible exception of 'The March of the Toys'.
What a pity. 'That Kleptomaniac Rag' conjures up all sorts of possibilities and the Scarecrow song from The Wizard of Oz makes you wonder how it compares with the later film version. Each page/month will give you plenty of time to ponder over how these sounded with the artists of the day and what little gems have been lost.

product_title: Optoma S311 Full 3D SVGA 3200 Lumen DLP Multimedia Projector with HDMI Ports
review_headline: GREAT projector, be careful with the audio
review_body:
I can't say enough good things about this projector. It's nearly silent most of of the time, the picture is crystal clear, runs great in Eco mode, and has just the right inputs (2 HDMI only) for home use. The USB port is perfect for powering a ChromeCast, and the switched audio out allows sound to follow picture.

The ONLY criticism that I have of this projector doesn't even relate to its ability to throw a picture up on a screen; there's no power spike buffer on the audio out, so if I leave my powered speakers turned on while powering up the projector, I get a nasty little power spike. Over time, that's going to do damage to the speakers. I'm still working on an equitable solution for my particular setup.

product_title: HSM Classic Strip-Cut Capacity Shredder
review_body: This shredder replaced many other shredders purchased from your local office supply chain store, which frequently overheated and broke. The HSM tackled our workload shredding paper and CDs, although I didn't find that it handled the capacity of sheets that it claimed. If the load is too heavy it will stop. Clicking the switch up and down didn't clear the jam. It was not an easy task to take the cover off to clear the jam. I needed long screwdrivers in order to reach in to unscrew the cover. The screws are attached to cheap plastic which easily snapped off when trying to lift the cover. Now the cover just sits on top, wobbling. This makes for an unsafe situation as the shredder still shreds. I agree with the other reviewers that the bag holder is awkward, the shredder is loud, the shred pieces are quite large and not that secure, and that HSM customer service is top notch. If this model corrected these issues it would be one awesome machine that I would purchase again, but at this point I will look for another comparable shredder.

product_title: Five Star 6 - Pocket Expanding File
review_headline: Great product, an essential for organization!
review_body:
Very good build and construction, it holds up well to normal wear and tear. It is one of the only quality expanding folders in the low storage capacity class (it has only 6 pockets). The only flaw that I find with the folder is that even though there are 6 pockets, you can only put five labels on because there is no label slot on the front plastic. Aside from this minor flaw, the folders are reinforced and we'll crafted. The locking mechanism is secure and easy to use, and a nice touch is the two pen slots on the front. It is a very reasonable price, and totally worth it.
Pros:
-6 pockets means sufficient storage
-Reinforced pockets
-Comes with labels for folders
-Durable construction
-Relatively cheap
-Quality locking mechanism
-2 pen holders
Cons:
-There are only 5 slots for the labels, even though there are 6 pockets
-Folders do not connect fully with the bottom of the expanding file

Overall it is a great product, the pros heavily outweigh the cons

product_title: Alvin EN48-4 Ensign Table, White Base/White Top 36" x 48", Angle adjustment from horizontal 0° to 90° with an adjustable height of 37" to 47"
review_headline: ... I could as overall I think this is an excellent product and I have only minor objections
review_body: I would rate this product at 4 and a half stars if I could as overall I think this is an excellent product and I have only minor objections.  I purchased the Alvin Ensign table with the 36x48” top in January 2015.  The set up and adjustment instructions were clear, the procedure straightforward and took less than an hour.  The product comes with a 17 mm open end wrench to adjust the lift-strength.  I would definitely suggest using a socket wrench with a short extension as the adjustment nut is recessed and would difficult to turn with the provided wrench.  As of this writing I have not used the table extensively and therefore cannot attest to how well it will hold up over time but I don’t anticipate that there should be any problems.  Visually, in my opinion, the table would not fit into the category of slick beautiful office furniture but it is a simple straightforward design and not objectionable.  The white paint is a little harsh (a little too blue).  I would have preferred a softer white such as used by Apple Computers or the Elfa shelving systems.  The adjustment procedure is an elegant concept and the mechanism works very well.  The table is quite sturdy and does not give when leaning on the edge.  There is a slight lateral jiggle but I don’t find it a big problem. If this gets worse over time I may choose to cross brace the frame with some light steel cable and turnbuckles. The current model that was shipped to me is slightly different from the image depicted online.  The brake lever is under the table top on the right edge which makes it easily accessible but not in a place where it is likely to be bumped and released unintentionally.  When researching this product I found a lack of dimensional information.  I’m providing some approximate dimensions here that may be useful in determining whether this product is appropriate for your purposes.  These dimensions are based on the 36”x48” top and thus some of them will be different with the smaller top.  In the horizontal orientation the table top can be adjusted from 37 ½” to 46” above the floor.  In the vertical orientation the top edge of the board can be adjusted from 48” – 69” above the floor.  With the table set at a 25 degree angle the front edge is 29” above the floor.  It would be ideal if the table went an inch or two lower, but even as it is I think one would be comfortable drafting when sitting in a low (20”) seat or standing.  Overall, a nice product that I would recommend to others.  Shop for the best price and lowest shipping costs.

I am loving this planner. This is definitely not your standard, rigid calendar... it's a holistic approach to planning your year, month and week. As a counselor-in-training, I am thoroughly impressed with the goal setting sections, self-discovery questions, and I especially love the boxes for "Intention of the Week" and "This Week I'm Grateful for..." This allows for mindful living while helping you to stay on track. Very helpful and definitely something I will recommend to my clients!

I've added post-it flags, so that I can easily flip to the month view and the weekly view, and I'm thinking of buying some stickers or color pens to add a little depth. I need something colorful to catch my attention (especially on days that bills are due!). I'm very very pleased with this product!

review_body: I sketch with mechanical pencils and I erase a lot! Most mechanical pencils have tiny, stubby erasers which can be hard to find when you need a new one. I purchased these Pentel Twist-Erase Pencils especially for the large erasers—and they even come with additional replacement erasers! How cool is that?!!! Glad these come in a two-pack. One of the pencils started to jam and got so stuck I couldn't even force out the lead. Apparently the non-retractable tip got a little bent and so the pencil stopped working. I drilled out the stuck lead using a pin-vise and was able to straighten the tip so I was good to go again. No more problems after that. I'm not fond of the Pentel leads that come with the pencils. I find that they require more pressure and are fairly light. I purchased some softer lead for my sketching.

product_title: Epson WorkForce  All-In-One Wireless Color Inkjet Printer WF-2540, Black
review_headline: Epic fail of a printer, and a bit of a funny story
review_body:
This printer was the biggest waste of space and time I have ever purchased from Amazon. I only wish to save all of you poor souls from having to go through the same experience. The printer overall looks great and the print quality is fine. So basic needs are met. Until you actually expect the wireless function to work after it goes to sleep. If the printer goes to sleep, so does the wireless connection, preventing you from actually printing anything. If you wake it up, there is a small chance that the wireless connection will reestablish itself, allowing you to use the printer as it is functionally designed to operate. I finally gave up and made up my mind to send this baby back to Amazon where I'm sure it will end up back in the hands of the good people at Epson who will probably just repackage it up and put it back in line to be purchased. Off it goes.

But oh, the irony. To return something to Amazon, you need to ACTUALLY PRINT A RETURN LABEL. It was almost as though this device had some sort of notion that it was headed someplace bad, and it simply refused to print the return label. One phone call into the Amazon customer service center later, despite its resistance to the idea of being repackaged and headed the same direction it came, it was sitting on the front porch, sans return label.

I only write this, dear Amazon friend, to prevent you from making the same mistake I did in purchasing this device. The wireless function was the main reason it went back, but in my short period of ownership, I did encounter a series of other challenges:

- Ridiculously and almost impossibly expensive and low volume print cartridges
- Fax function operated at circa 1992 speeds, and failed consistently at page 19/20. Twice.
- Above mentioned fax function also seems to chew up pages in the document feeder just for fun
- The Epson software that ships with this device installed no less than 9 different applications on my PC, most seemingly associated with the ever important fax function

product_title: Voltage Valet Quick Caf? II (Travel Coffee Maker)
review_headline: Know A Few Quirks and Ready to Go!
review_body:
We've had this small, light machine for over two years and now take it everywhere we go. Regarding the world voltage switch, we used a "P-Touch" sticker to remind us to 'check the voltage.' Problem solved for "wrong voltage selected." The "on" switch requires a firm push, so it's nearly impossible to accidentally turn on. Another plus is that the machine turns itself off after brewing, so there are no worries about accidentally leaving it on. We have also made continuous cups and do not have to wait the 10-15 minutes between brews like another reviewer stated.

The machine was initially bought as a gift so my man could have some decent coffee in Afghanistan and anywhere else he would be deployed to. Because they had decent coffee available, he used the machine as a hot water dispenser for tea and oatmeal in his room. He said the tea was a great way to start his one half day off a week and a hot meal at any time was nice. Like other reviews, he did say that it wasn't great for coffee because it would sputter out and make a mess, and did not have time to experiment on the best grounds combination.

When he returned to the States, the machine sat in its case because coffee was readily available again and figured there was no use for it. As we started traveling around, I had him pack the machine so we would not have to "look for coffee" when desired. To avoid the sputtering (because we still hadn't experimented on the best grounds amount), the machine was packed with Starbucks Via, creamer packets/cups, and sugar packets. Voila - good, easy coffee with no mess clean up. Bottled water is poured into the unit and a cup with the Via is at the other end ready to be made. He would go and brush his teeth and when done with morning duties, his coffee would be ready and waiting. Oddly enough, this routine has made the process even easier because no cleanup is required and each beverage is portioned out.

Now that there is more time, we are experimenting on the grounds ratio "just to know," but honestly, the Via protocol is "our way" to go. We do know that grounded coffee is cheaper, but when "on the go," it works well for us. The coffee is bought on sale to bring down costs further and sugar/creamer packets are usually available at hotels and/or we use our own (that's brought). No matter how we look at it, this method is still more convenient and economical than looking for it. Friends who have traveled with us were impressed with the size and taste.

And on a final note, at the airport, I saw a man bring a "small" coffee machine through TSA that took up most of his backpack. I almost laughed aloud and then told him about my treasured find. Once we figured out how to make the machine work well for us, we have never looked back.

product_title: E-Z Ink Remanufactured Ink Cartridge Replacement for Epson 252XL High Capacity, 4 Black, 2 Cyan, 2 Magenta, 2 Yellow
review_headline: but it was a complete waste of time and my hand is blue & red ...
review_body:
I thought I was going to save some money by buying a re-manufactured ink cartridge, but it was a complete waste of time and my hand is blue & red from trying to fix it. I installed the cyan cartridge, but it wasn't really printing-- so my images were coming out really red :\ After searching for a solution, the usual solution was (1) removing extra labels (2) clean printer head (3) remove and reinstalling the cartridges or (4) turn your printer on/off.

Well, I continue to do that continuously for about a day and a half (yes, I'm very persistent). I kept trying to clean the printer head -- which I found was the most common solution. And I didn't think any of it until *bam* all of the sudden my printer told me to change my Black cartridge -- and that was my 'real' epson 252XL (yes! full XL!).

So, after trying for so long to get the cyan cartridge to work -- i've wasted all my Black cartridge (MFG ~$35). *sigh* total fail on my part.

... so my warning to all buyers, if it works-- awesome. But beware and don't clean the printer head so much -- because you're actually wasting lots of ink!!

Printer: Epson WF-2640 (purchased April 2015)

review_headline: Perfect for a professional rosarian or home gardener!

They also allow for finer motor skills, such as tying string. I bought my first pair about a year ago and with continual use over that time, I only had a couple of nicks and a quarter inch tear to report (and the tear made no difference in their performance). I just got a new pair to start off a new season and now I can hand down my old pair to whoever works alongside me! As would be expected, the only time I've had a prickle really get me is if I grab it head on - but the prickle needs to be massive to actually pierce through. Highly recommend!

product_title: GoWrite! Dry Erase Self-Adhesive Roll
review_headline: You get what you pay for. This one has some decent value to it.
review_body:
Keep in mind -- you get what you pay for.
20 bucks for 40 sq ft of dry erase surface -- or go and spend 200-300 bucks on a hard-surface equivalent.

I bought this, even after reading the other reviews claiming that it sticks to nothing, falls easily, etc...and if you're trying to place it on a schools cinderblock wall, then I completely understand why it is falling, because those surfaces are very porous (lots of little holes in the cinderblock, allowing air to get beneath the surface).
If you're trying to hang it up in your classroom, and you have these types of walls, use it to build your own actual whiteboard, by getting a sheet of light-weight wood or something...place this onto that wood, and then hang the home-made whiteboard up.

With that in mind, most of the other reviews are correct...this does have a bit of trouble sticking once it is up (I have multiple bubbles in it, from just having it up over night.)...however the bublbes don't actually interfere with writing. They're just there...and is acceptable for a $20 writing surface.

As for the falling issue? One nail or thumbtack in each corner solves that.

I'm giving it 5 stars, for the value.
20 bucks, and you get a useful writing surface that does exactly what is intended, and you get a large amount of it. However, I wouldn't recommend it if you're after the quality of a $200-300 whiteboard.

product_title: HP Laserjet  M177FW Wireless All-in-One Color Printer
review_body:
I should've headed the warnings from previous reviewers. This printer is indeed a piece of junk. Like so many before me, I was stuck with the infinite "Initializing" screen right out-of-the-box, brand-new, never-used. After an hour of restarting and trying different outlets (as the official HP forums will have you do), I figured out that by removing the front toner cartridge and re-inserting it, I was able to get past that screen.

It seemed all was well and I was happily doing test prints. Until I tried to switch it off, and move it to the cabinet I was planning to use for it. The problem was back! My previous solution worked again but by now confidence in this piece of equipment was severely eroded.

Then the very first time it was on for long enough to fall asleep (go into low-power mode), it disappeared from my wired network and would not wake up when sending it a print job. This could only be remedied by doing a full restart of the device. After that I tried tens of cycles of letting it fall asleep and trying to wake it up with a print job from different devices on my network. It wakes up about 50% of the time, and the other 50% it requires a full restart. The origin of the print job makes no difference.

I'm returning this junk heap back to Amazon and will not buy another piece of HP consumer equipment again. HP's line of business printers are incredible and work fantastic. Their consumer stuff has slid so far down the slope of cost-cutting as to be completely worthless at this point.

product_title: White Chalk Markers Set of 4 - Fine 3mm Reversible Tip - Chalkboard Pen or Glass Marker for Back to School Classroom Organization, Window Decor & More - Dust Free Liquid Chalk - 100% Quality Guarantee
review_body: I love liquid chalk markers!  I am a teacher who dislikes chalk, so when I discovered liquid chalk markers, I became addicted. I use these daily in my classroom ~ on the chalkboard, dry erase boards, construction paper, desks...the list could go on and on. The SketchIt White Liquid Chalk Marker Set has provided my students and I with many hours of learning and fun. I use them to write messages to my students, as well as on my dry erase board when delivering instruction. The students use them to write on their dry erase boards, to write on their desks, and most recently on construction paper when doing a Mother's Day project. I received this product at a discount in exchange for my unbiased review. I love these markers because they can be used and cleaned off of most surfaces in my classroom. The brilliantly white color is easy to see from a distance and doesn't come off unless I choose to clean it off with a wet cloth. If the liquid chalk gets on your clothes, it easily wipes off and doesn't stain. SketchIt White Liquid Chalk Markers are 100% water based and don't produce dust. They are easy to store and work immediately when I need them. I store them horizontally in a plastic tub so that my students and I can grab them quickly. The dual tip design allows me to make bold or fine lines based on my preference. They can be used to leave messages, decorate, and for crafts. SketchIt White Liquid Chalk Markers are a great addition to my classroom.

product_title: Brother Printer MFC-J6520DW Wireless Color Printer with Scanner, Copier and Fax
review_headline: Print quality leaves a lot to be desired...
review_body:
I did a lot of research and read a lot of reviews before purchasing this item. I chose it over the two tray version because of the price difference for the few differences you get (am on a tight budget). Now that I have used it a few times I am not all that happy with it.
I have printed: regular text printing
large format print, mostly colored text
tshirt transfers
photos on cardstock
photo and text on cards (avery foldable cards)

The good:
-easy to read control panel
-prints rather quickly
-large format paper (the main reason I bought it)
-price was good

The bad:
-it is large, but I knew that and have room to accommodate it
-not very user friendly print commands and hard to customize

The ugly:
-manual feed tray is at the back of the unit so hard to get your paper fed back there and you can only put in one sheet at a time
-the manual feed tray feeds the paper crooked, when it feeds it
-so far, every time I tried to feed a paper on the manual feed tray the printer fails to read it and I have to remove and replace a couple of times.
-photo quality is crap. I set the print to best and photo and the colors are still blah and edges are not crisp. this is on regular paper and cardstock. (have not tried glossy photo paper).
-I was trying to print on both sides of avery cards and it keeps getting stuck trying to print the back side. I've tried both the main tray (got stuck right away) and the manual feed tray (got stuck on back side). Not sure why it claims it can do this when it has not worked for me at all.

All in all I bought this hoping to add some flair to my home-based business and make my own cards. Has been a disappointment in every special thing I try to print, particularly pictures. Very sad, and now I'm stuck with it thanks to my tight budget that I was trying to help by printing my own marketing materials! Ha! Definitely would not buy again, maybe not any Brother brand due to poor print quality.
I tried to print on both sides of, maybe not any Brother brand due to poor print quality.

product_title: WorkEZ Executive - ergonomic laptop stand, monitor riser, standing desk
review_body:
I absolutely love this laptop stand. Because of neck issues, I needed to find a modification as I am on the computer almost every day. I took a chance on the WorkEZ Executive stand and I am very impressed. When I first took it out of the box, I thought, "You have got to be kidding me." The stand is super light, but durable.

I do want to put my review in context - I almost always use my laptop in one position and have a wireless keyboard and mouse. The few times when I have typed quickly directly on the laptop, the metal holder feels a little bouncy but nothing significant. The stand itself is quite sturdy.

For people who need more flexibility in positions, there are a wide range of options from which to choose in terms of height and angles. There are numbers on the side of each "joint" so that you know if the stand is level. For someone challenged like me when it comes to mechanical things, this comes in handy when trying to figure out the ideal setup.

My boyfriend, who also spends his day on the computer, fell in love with my stand. He suffered from eye strain, eye strain headaches, and fatigue using his laptop the conventional way. Being the engineer that he is, he has played with the stand far more than I have and absolutely loves it. He no longer has the eye strain, headaches, and fatigue. As with me, he uses a wireless keyboard and mouse.

Bottom line, for people with wireless keyboards and mouses, go for it! You'll need to read reviews of people who type directly for their opinions. I would buy this as a gift for a family member or friend in a heartbeat.

review_body:
buy one even if you're not sure what you'll use it for .. you'll think of something.
at the moment I use them as "hard" VPN endpoints for secure things .. you can even use the SD card or USB for a HSM.
the unit is the size of a deck of cards, the adapter adds half-again as much height .. so it's like a small paperback that plugs into the wall.

Fwiw : Globalscale (the mfr) will work with you if you are doing embedded development, this is sort of a developer's starter kit .. when you finalize the design email them you can get simpler versions run for production at lower cost. For a tinkering person though these are a good thing to have.

product_title: Adjustable Shower Head Holder with Suction Cup Chrome Bracket
review_headline: So many problems, so little time...
review_body:
First, this took FOREVER to get here b/c it came from CHINA, which was not posted on there when I ordered it. I have ordered things on e_ay from China and it is always clearly marked. This leads to the second problem: there was NO ENGLISH WHATSOEVER on the packaging. I used common sense & comments from other suction cup items and cleaned off the shower wall with rubbing alcohol to ensure a good grip, but that's all I could do: guess.

I wanted to like this. It seemed substantial for being plastic (it's not metal), and the suction *appeared* like it would be solid. My shower head hangs very high on our wall, and we are all short, so I was hoping this would be perfect. However, issue #3 was that my VERY AVERAGE Water Pic shower nozzle was just about too large for it. You could sort of shove it in, but I worried that over time, that would probably break the plastic. I thought that maybe that could be solved by just leaving it there and not moving it around too much, but problem #4 was that it puts the water stream coming out at you almost horizontal! No joke. It cannot adjust down b/c of that orange tab that locks the suction.

Which is issue #5: it came flying off the wall (with running shower nozzle attached) while using it, 2 days later! Seriously?! I have crappy Dollar Store suction cups that stay on better. And those are just cheap, not great. I paid eight bux for this, waited weeks for it to get here, and have had nothing but problems! Not only am I out the cash, but I'm back to square one with my too-high shower hook. Sigh...

product_title: Chalkboard Labels Complete Bundle: 73 Premium Stickers for Jars + Erasable White Chalk Marker. The BEST Large and Reusable Chalkboard Labels + Liquid Chalk Pen to Decorate Your Pantry Storage & Office
review_headline: Cute chalkboard accents, without the hassle of chalkboard paint.
review_body:
I have had a blast labeling different things in the house and have a cupboard door that is covered with chalkboard contact paper to help one of my daughters with her weekly chores. I just write everything up the begining of the week, and she ticks them off as she does them. A few good swipes wth a damp rag washes away the chalk, and a few swipes with a dry rag and we are ready to go again. The pen does take a bit to get working at first with having to press down a few times so that the tip goes up into the pen to get the liquid chalk flowing, same as when using liquid highlighters.

The stickers are the perfect size for my white canisters. I am always washing them, and roating what each one has, so being able to wipe of and re-label is awesome. I even threw some contact paper on a small box and slapped one of these on it with Laundry Bags so I now have a cute storage box for all my delicates baggies, instead of just thrown on top of the dryer.

The chalk ink does take a few minutes to dry fully I've found that it is best for me to place the sticker on what I want to label, smooth it out, then write on it. I sadly don't have the patience to write while it's on the sheet and then leave it to dry. The stickers have been staying put, and several of them have been wiped down with a damp cloth to clean and rewritten on. I like the variety of patterns available, and want to see what damage I can do with some scrapbooking.

I've not yet removed any stickers and tried to use them somewhere else. With 40 stickers, I'm not sure this will ever happen. They are a pretty study sticker and are holding up well with abuse in the kitchen.

I did receive this product for free in exchage for a review; however all opinions are my own.

product_title: HP 56 (C9319FN) Black Original Ink Cartridges, 2 pack
review_body: UPDATE: 08 May 2017 - Ordered again and got some with a March 2018 expiry. Move to 4 stars.  UPDATE: 08 July 2015 - The expired cartridges are working fine after doing many prints without issues. From 1 star to 3 stars for the below stated reasons.  I received these cartridges in a sealed envelope which contained the 2 HP56's wrapped in white protective envelopes and not in a box as pictured. Having used these cartridges for years I know they come in a box (as pictured) and have the expiration date printed on the box. Therefore, one cannot tell the expiry date unless opening the white protective envelope to examine the cartridge. Upon checking both, it read; 2010/04/26...expired. Now I have used expired cartridges before with no issues but those were about a year old and that I had in my stationery stock. They were purchased with expiry dates yet to come and certainly not almost 5 years old as is the current case.  I will update my review after using one to advise if it works. 1 star for now for not getting my ink in the HP box , not being advised of the expiry date and for the sale of expired ink.

product_title: Hanging Banner Holder Mounts From The Ceiling, Silver Satin Aluminum, Displays, 72-Inch Wide Banners - 72 x 1 x 5/8-Inch
review_body:
This poster holder works reasonably well. The spring to hold the bars shut is extremely strong, which is good for holding your poster or sign up without slipping, but for such a long bar that is a bit of a problem -- it's very hard to open the holder without bending the bars, it's delicate to get the poster aligned, and the bar snaps closed with such force that it tends to eject the poster slightly and mess up your alignment or even rip it. It's a very delicate operation that requires some real hand strength.

The hooks that are afixed to the bars to mount the holder on the wall are extremely flimsy. One of them was broken on my item, but it doesn't seem worth it to send it back. I'm hoping some superglue will fix it well enough to hold!

Finally, be aware that this package does not include any mounting hooks or brackets. That also means you will have to judge the weight and choose appropriate drywall anchors if you are mounting on drywall, since there isn't a mounting kit included. All easy enough, but worth knowing in advance that you will need more supplies.

review_body: all of the problems that i was experiencing  such as buttons locking up, numbers not showing up on display and numbers that were blocked still ringing the phone are addressed in the latest version of the FAQ's and the operators manual found at their web site. I tried all of the series and parallel hook up configurations with limited success.  I had to finally hook it up in parallel and then not use my DSL filter on that phone jack in order to get it to work with any consistency. I still have one blocked number that seems to get through unimpeded, but all of the other numbers I have listed stop coming in after one ring. It is not complete silent satisfaction, but it it better than it was before the blocker. I do like some of the features offered such as its small size and hitting the CID redial on your phone to input a manual number into the block list. Maybe future upgrades will reduce current frustrations on a potentially fantastic product.

product_title: Rapesco ECO X5 Less Effort Stapler - Soft White, 90 sheet(1400)
review_headline: Staples a wide range of pages -- if you buy the right range of staples!
review_body:
This is a good mid-range stapler that allows you to staple a lot more pages than your average stapler.

Pros:
-Easy to push down through 40+pages
-Quiet
-Handles a wide range of pages -- BUT -- see the first Con below

Cons:
- While it will staple 2-90 sheets, you have to use different staples to achieve that full range. The table on the bottom of the stapler itself explains:
2-30pp --> 24/6mm Hard Wire staples
30-50pp --> 923/8mm staples
40-70pp --> 923/10mm staples
60-90pp --> 923/12mm staples
(If you use a higher range staple with fewer pages, it will still work, but you'll have the pointy ends of the staples sticking up through the front of your papers.)
- It's not staggeringly attractive -- but really, do you choose your semi-heavy-duty staplers on the basis of their appearance? I guess you might -- but to me, if it does the job, that's the important thing, and this does!
- You can't open it fully to use it like a staple gun, so you can only staple fairly close to the edge of any stack -- I can't, for example, staple the center of a booklet made from 8.5x11in paper, folded in the center.

review_headline: Your best bet for quality highlighting on the go.
review_body:
I'm obsessed. As a graduate student with an unhealthy obsession for office supplies, I'm definitely a fan for life. The ink quality isn't as perfect as Staedtler (Sharpie smear written text a bit, Staedtler doesn't at all), but over all, these might be the winner

Pros:
- Bright yellow color, barely fades
- Pen clip lets you stick in pockets or bags and stay in place
- clicky top is convenient when you are on the go, no worries about losing caps
- fairly washable. I forgot to click up the highlighter one day and put it in my white coat for a couple hours and had a HUGE yellow spot over my boob. Some alcohol took out a good portion of it at work, and then the washing machine took out the rest when i got home. My coat is still pristine!

Cons
- will smear written ink a little, no matter how dry it is. Not enough to be illegible, but might annoy the more type-A personalities out there. Perfectly fine over printed text.
