product_title: Esky ES012 2.4G Wireless+USB wired Cordless Handheld Automatic Laser Bar code Bar Code Scanner Reader for Windows devices (32-bit Decoder, 1500mAh Rechargeable Battery, 256K Storage Memory)
review_headline: Great Scanner but the Manual Needs Corrections and Here They ARE!
review_body:
I have given this barcode scanner 4 stars only because of errors in the manual which make it difficult to understand on receipt. These errors are for the CT-007 Barcode Scanner Manual. In Function Setup Barcodes, the "Enter Setup" and the "Exit with Save" setup codes are reversed. That is, you must shoot the code on the left titled "Exit with Save" in order to Enter Setup and you must shoot the code labeled "Enter Setup" in order to Exit with Save. In other words, ON is OFF and OFF is ON. Whether you are entering OR exiting, you will hear 3 descending beeps. If you are in setup mode, you will hear 3 ascending beeps when a configuration change is registered. Also, the Enable EAN-13 and Disable EAN-13 codes are reversed.
The setup card for inventory function is totally unrelated to the manual. You do not need to enter configuration mode in order to shoot the codes on the card to determine if you are going to write to your computer immediately, or store the values in the scanner and write them later. Normal writes to your computer immediately. Inventory mode stores the data for later. "Uploading Statistics" will write the total number of records in memory (which would be handy if you want to ensure you have enough rows in your spreadsheet for the data dump). "Data upload" will dump the data to your computer (but retain it in scanner flash memory. "Clear" will clear the flash memory. All-in-all, the scanner does what it is supposed to do and has no difficulty reading whatever of the available codes you throw at it, so long as you have them enabled.
One more thing. Some have complained it doesn't have a stand. Nope. It doesn't. But it will stand up straight on it's flat-bottomed handle. If you point it towards yourself, you may not feel lonely if you are working alone. :-)

product_title: Pentel Arts GraphGear 1000 Premium Gift Set with Refill Leads & Erasers
review_headline: Great Pencil, I use it everyday
review_body:
This is probably the best mechanical pencil I have ever owned. I'm not saying this to be overly dramatic. This is the best pencil I've used. It is perfectly balanced, and feels great in the hand. It has a solid feel, and has some weight to it. It is comfortable to hold, and glides across paper when writing.

My handwriting has improved from using this pencil. I actually use it as my everyday pencil to do hw, take exams, and doodle. The retractable tip is a great feature, because as most people have experienced, if the metal tip on a mechanical pencil is always out, it will end up stabbing either your hand or your leg if you put it in your pocket. The ability to have the lead type labeled is also useful for those who use different hardness leads.

While the eraser is small (typical of drafting pencils), I do this find it a nuisance when using as my main pencil. I just use a big eraser and use the pencil's eraser for more precise erasing.

The build quality is very good, and 've dropped it numerous times and it hasn't shown any signs of breaking. The grip is also surprisingly comfy. It really is just a bumpy metal with gel ovals, but it does the trick in a minimalist way.

I highly recommend this pencil even if you have no intention of using it for drafting or drawing. Multiple friends liked it so much that they went and bought their own.

product_title: Epson Expression Home XP-400 Wireless All-in-One Color Inkjet Printer, Copier, Scanner.  Prints from Tablet/Smartphone. AirPrint Compatible (C11CC07201)
review_headline: I desperately wanted this to be a great product.  It's not.
review_body:
The only reason I am giving it two stars instead of one is because the scan quality is very good. Other than that, I have never had more problems with a printer in my entire life. The Wi-Fi keeps popping offline, which pretty much defeats the entire reason for the purchase, as I wanted wireless so I could move from room to room.

As for the printer itself, it worked fine, at first, but then, when it came time to replace the black ink cartridge, it went south and never fully recovered. Just to get it to print a simple black-ink document takes multiple nozzle checks and head-cleaning sessions as the printer seems to magically lose it's ability to print when it sits. Maybe it's become self-aware and is bored and lonely and seeking revenge for being ignored; I really couldn't say. But I've tried everything from completely replacing all four ink cartridges to uninstalling and re-installing the software; nothing works.

I am quite disappointed, too, because I was told Epson was the end-all be-all for printing photographs. Back to Canon, it is, I guess.

product_title: Pentel Hi-polymer Block Eraser, Large, 3 Pack, White  (ZEH10BP3-K6)
review_headline: Flexible, effective and gentle to the paper...
review_body:
There is not much one can say about an eraser. I bought this triple pack (the large option) for my preschooler kids who started going through activity books. All I can say is my kids are pretty harsh using pencils and sometimes do their activities with colored pencils instead of the regular ones ( somehow these colored ones are tougher to erase) So these erasers have been tested in extremes and have performed well so far.

They are solid( do not crumble like the cheap erasers I used in my childhood) but flexible enough so that it does not harm the paper (I would call this one among the softer erasers I have used.) We sometimes have to keep erasing the same spot over and over but surprisingly, so far I have not seen a significant deformity on the paper caused by the eraser.

For a little over $1.5 per eraser, it is not the cheapest on the market but for me it is OK due to the superior quality. I would buy it again

product_title: Avery Mini Durable Binder for 5.5 x 8.5 Inch Pages, 2-Inch Round Ring, Black, 1 Binder (27554)
review_headline: If your a Writer and take notes on a Portable 7 Ring Franklin Covey Binder, this binder is great to store referenced information
review_body:
This is a great binder for putting in my monthly writings into. I've been writing for the longest on paper, through my personal Franklin Covey Classic 7 ring binder, after trying various apps (although I started officially writing in 2Do app on my iphone and Mac).

As the months go by, I would put into this Avery Mini Binder as reference book. So far I have for 2014 and filling up a new through another purchase of this binder for this year 2015, eXample I have up to February right now. I have to go over my March journal/notes/todo's/drawing/etc. before transferring the paperwork. I know, I should do this process at least once a week, as David Allen states to do within Getting Things Done (the weekly review). That is as hard as he states, but in time I'm getting better with that.

I hope this helps those who write alot and wish to organize/reference properly.

product_title: Panasonic DECT 6.0 Link-to-Cell via Bluetooth Cordless Phone with Answering System
review_body: I bought this phone because despite having four cell phones in the house,  often when I try to call someone,  either their phone was on silent or it was in a different room,  etc. so no one would answer.  As a result,  I figured if we had multiple handsets strategically set up in various rooms throughout the house and connected to a couple of the cell phones,  they will hear when I call regardless of where the cell phones were.  This phone set definitely served this purpose well.  I only have it the stars however,  because the sound clarity could be a bit better and there seems to be a delay when talking to someone. At times,  it gets so frustrating that we would switch from the Panasonic handset to the crll phone in the middle of the call of just pick up the call on the cell phone rather than using one of the handsets. Setting up the Bluetooth connection is also a little challenging. Overall though,  it does the job.

product_title: Epson Expression Inkjet Printers
review_body:
I tried this for several types of print (plain letter quality paper, photographic paper of an 8 x 10 and a 4 x 6) as well as copying. It was sampled with various Bluetooth devices (Apple and HTC phones) as well as OS and Explorer. The end judgment is that it is a solid, workmanlike printer/copier/scanner for the budget conscious.

Full sized photos were full of lines and altogether poor in quality, however, 4 x 6 prints turned out better with far less detectable lines. All the regular print/copy/scan features worked well enough, if not of the finest reproductive quality. It linked up to our devices once the software/app was downloaded, and we printed wirelessly straight from our device's photo cache.

While I wouldn't use this as my go-to printer for photo printing or when you need letter-sized crisp prints, it does work as a general function, middling quality printer otherwise. For the current $69.99 price, it seems a solid bargain.

If your expectation is to obtain very high resolution JPG like the ones you can get from you digital camera, this photo scanner will not satisfy your requirements. I suggest to buy the standard products avoiding to buy more accessories like the 2nd or 3rd slide support (too expensive). product_title: Student Driver Red & White - 12 in x 6 in - Laminated Sign Alert Warning Sticker
review_headline: Does its job, get a plastic card handy to have a nice smooth application.
review_body:
The sticker utilizes a one sided adhesive, just peel off the backing and stick it onto any surface. Pretty noticeable and sturdy. Upon taking it off after 3 weeks or so being under the Texas heat, there was no damage to the sticker nor car. There was no left over residue while peeling and the sticker had an extremely high stretch threshold. Looks great on a black car with the strong contrast of black, white, and red. A lot of people may give you some space and patience, while others may try to tease you more with these types of stickers. Nonetheless, its great as a warning sticker and great for first time drivers, students, or those getting used to a different class of cars.

Tip: When placing these types of stickers on your car, clean the car surface first. Slowly apply the sticker at one end first and with a plastic card (id, old credit card, membership card, etc) smooth out the sticker from one end to the next to avoid air bubbles. This sticker can be taken off fairly easily, so don't be afraid if you mess up. Just peel back and use a plastic car to smooth the sticker back onto the car surface.

product_title: Fujitsu ScanSnap
review_body:
What a great scanner! This scanner/software bundle Just Works. In the midst of a huge move, I decided I had to do something about all the file cabinets of paperwork that I'd always planned on scanning and filing online. I bought the ScanSnap based on various reviews. When it arrived, I put it to work immediately, and the scanner exceeded my hopes. I was able to load the scanner with all manner of documents--tax documents, old receipts, you name it--and the ScanSnap sucked everything through quickly and turned it into a useful pdf. It sensed blank pages and eliminated them. I then decided to load the scanner up with the mountain of old business cards that had accumulated over the years, and within a half an hour, they were all converted into the included CardMinder app.
My only complaint (and this is minor) is that the interface for handling the resulting files is not as efficient as the rest of the process. I found the naming options to be limited, and the Mac software didn't always respond to mouse clicks accurately. When compared to the rest of the process, this aspect stuck out as less than optimal. It impeded an otherwise fast and intuitive procedure.

product_title: Samsung SL-M2070FW/XAA Wireless Monochrome Printer with Scanner, Copier and Fax
review_headline: We're happy with it - it's a keeper
review_body:
researched a ton of printers, and settled on this one. We are not concerned with faxing/scanning at this time - may look into it next.

Basically wanted printer and copier. Was having an issue with my ipad and iphone printing to it and did online live support chat. She basically took an hour to update drivers and I was still back where we started. If you go into the actual Samsung App it will print fine to the printer, but doesn't appear to print outside of the App from Ipad or Iphone. Which is a pain.

Setup went relatively well. Used the install disk on both our PCs. The wireless capabilty was a snap as the printer was always found. Had a glitch with the firmware update hanging (scan section) and ended up just cancelling after an hour (which they say dont do). A later check on the site says our firmware is up to date. Whatever, not sure I believe it. Did hit a recyling problem after the driver update - but after printing a sheet the machine settled down.
Print quality is fine, setup was painless for the most part onto our WiFi network. Had my first paper jam and had to check the manual to get it all out (really a jam!!)

Size is good, powers up when you print (don't have to walk over to office to wake it up first), quality ok for us. The machine suits us fine for home use. I am happy as a lark to be back to a toner cartridge instead of all those dang inkjets.

review_headline: the case is very sturdy. The three cards fit very well (my driver's ...
review_body:
So far, the case is very sturdy.

The three cards fit very well (my driver's license, and two credit cards); the credit cards are face-to-face with the number on opposite sides. I can actually get a fourth card (smooth on both sides) in if I need to. I would like some retention mechanism for the cards against the phone so I could use the back as a kickstand like the description suggests.

The case's volume buttons align with the actual phone's buttons better than the Otterbox on my work phone. The speaker is partially covered by the cards, but that is to be expected (there is no space the size of a credit card

The image is degrading a bit (mostly on the sharper edges, and where it first impacts when set/dropped on a counter). The product image makes the back look glossy, but it is actually a matte finish and slightly darker than shown.

All in all, this is a very good case:
Sturdy
Well-fitted
Clear image on back
No floppy wallet bit to make it awkward
Fits in a car dock/holder

product_title: Generic Bluecell 5pcs Gun Smoke Color 5.5 Inch Aircraft Key Ring Holder Wire
review_headline: Nice for keychains and other various uses
review_body:
Very nice for the price, you can't argue with how cheap these things are. Mine were all the same and were the length advertised. From reading other reviews, it sounds like some people had different experiences. As with any of these generic products with most of the sellers shipping from Taiwan/ China, it's going to vary sometimes depending on the seller. Choose a seller with a decent rating and you should be sent what you actually ordered.

The wire is bare but it's well clamped at the end so there's nothing rough to snag pockets or anything. They're pretty easy to connect and disconnect but if you're doing this multiple times a day you probably want something quicker. I imagine they would wear out quicker if you're unthreading them hundreds of times too since the threads are pretty small.

They seem reasonably strong but they obviously aren't intended to hold any kind of weight. The size when looped is a little larger than most keychains but it makes up for it by flexing and laying flat in your pocket.

product_title: Avery Big Tab Insertable Three-Pocket Corner Lock Plastic Dividers, 5 Multicolor Tabs, 1 Set (11273)
review_headline: Almost Perfect in Every Way [4.5 Stars]
review_body:
These plastic dividers are flexible, strong, the holes are well-punched (i.e. they fit and turn easily in a standard 3-ring binder), and the pockets fit a variety of paper sizes.

It includes a sheet with 18 labels (if you fold them in half as directed, 36 if you use each label individually) and the sheet is perforated in the center so you can run each half through the printer separately. This, however, only works if your printer can handle half sheets (i.e. 8.5\\"x5.5\\"). There's also a downloadable template for Word*. (Search for \\"Big Tab Insertable Dividers 5 Tab\\" on the Avery site instead of by product number and make sure to test on a plain sheet of paper first to ensure it will line up properly with the labels.)

Tip: If you know you'll be running the labels through the printer more than once, draft your labels from the bottom up so you'll be able to remove those used labels and still be able to feed the sheet through the printer again.

I tested the labels in both inkjet and laser printers and neither jammed or smudged. I also tested the leftover labels with ballpoint, liquid ink, marker, and pencil, each of which worked well. The perforations on each of the labels allowed for clean separation and each label fit into their tab perfectly. Plus, once the labels are in, they stay in until you remove them.

The tabs extend beyond the binder's cover, which I appreciate as it allows me to quickly see the sections without needing to open the binder cover, and the corner lock feature is fabulous at keeping papers from slipping out regardless of which way the binder's turned. What makes me sad, though, is that the corner lock is only available for the back pocket, so papers in the front two pockets can and will slip out if the binder is tipped. Another qualm I have is with the opacity of the blue and purple dividers--they're dark enough to hamper reading the labels (not badly, but enough).

Overall, these are solid dividers. If not for the corner lock and opacity situation, these would be as close to perfect as perfect can be.

* The Word (.doc) template doesn't play nicely with some alternate word processing programs (i.e. OpenOffice or Google Docs), so depending on your program, it may be easier to create your own template for Photoshop or your word processing program specifically, which is the route I ended up choosing.ty situation, these would be as close to perfect as perfect can be. * The Word (.doc) template doesn't play nicely with some alternate word processing programs (i.e. OpenOffice or Google Docs), so depending on your program, it may be easier to create your own template for Photoshop or your word processing program specifically, which is the route I ended up choosing.

review_body:

I bought another portable scanner (about the same size) by another well known manufacturer for about $90 less money, but this one is far better in terms of speed, ease of use, overall quality, and ease of scanning into the cloud or other programs, etc. Fujitsu is he clear winner when it comes to scanners.

HOWEVER, one thing you need to know is that this is a simplex (single side) scanner. The S1100 is about $65 higher priced, and that is because it is a duplex (double sided) scanner. If you don't mind turning the sheet over and feeding it again, this will work fine for you.

product_title: Wagner SwissPen Classic. Black handle SP134
review_headline: Carried mine for 10 years as a Captain with my fire department! Never failed me..
review_body: I have had one of these for over 10 years. I carried mine in my fire department turnouts, and used it in all types of situations for filling out patient report forms, taking notes, etc... I used it in the rain, and the thing never failed me. My fellow firefighters learned to ask me if they could borrow my pen, because they either forgot theirs, or the one they had didn't work. I retired 4 years ago, and this now resides in my car. It comes in handy when I get a package from Amazon that I need to open! I recommend these pens...for anyone!

product_title: 8780 Line Power Speaker Phone
review_body: We bought our first Cortelco 8780 Line Power Speaker Phone 2 years ago and we like it so much we got another for our upstairs office a few months ago. Glad to have both of them.  Pros: * Line Power! You don't need a wall plug to power this phone, so there's less clutter/wires on your desk, plus you don't have to place it near an outlet. * Good, nice-sized LED display. Nothing fancy, but easy to read. Shows the date and time * Straight-forward to program. Has built-in address and phone book. * The buttons have a very solid, sturdy, but smooth action when you depress them, and they rebound nicely. Quality feel. * Light flashes on the phone when you have voice-mail. I know the under-40 crowd doesn't care about this (what's voice mail?), but we adults still answer our phone messages, so it's good to know when you have messages to pick up. * Very sturdy, durable phone. Our first one is in the kitchen, and is used by everyone--kids, adults, guests. It gets dropped, spilled on, and generally subjected to our family's chaos. Cleans up perfectly, looks nice, and seems to be unbreakable. * Nicely engineered handset. You can talk on this for a long time and it feels comfortable. Well designed.  Cons: *You can turn the ringer volume down, but you can't turn it off. Bummer if you're trying to sleep in and someone calls you early.

product_title: U.S. Art Supply 9" x 12" Premium Manga-Marker Paper Pad, 60 Pound (100gsm), Pad of 24-Sheets (Pack of 2 Pads)
review_headline: My little artist loves this paper!
review_body:
If you have a artist in the family, especially one that likes to create with markers..this is the best paper around!

It is great paper for drawing with ink pens or pencils, permanent markers, and with using mixed dry media. The pad has 24 sheets of white paper that has a shiny finish. It is actually designed to use with markers so the shiny finish brings out all of your color choices in a vibrant way. It is acid free, with a PH balance that will allow your pictures to last without fading.

I think the greatest feature is that it is bleed proof. The colors won’t run into each other or bleed through to the back like so many other types of paper.

UPDATED 2/25/2016
We have ordered several of these pads over the last 6-8 months. They are really nice and hold up well. I like them best for using with gel pens and markers as they don't tear or bleed through.

Overall, I would recommend this paper to anyone that is either heavy handed like I am when drawing or if you are using markers.

I hope you enjoyed this review. If you have any questions about my experience please leave me a comment. I will be happy to follow up on my experience with this product.

As a blogger, I am often provided product samples by companies at a reduced price for consideration and/or review purposes. Regardless, I only recommend products or services I use personally and believe will be good for others. I refuse to review or endorse products that I have not or will not personally try. Needless to say, I may be a product reviewer but my thoughts are my own and the discount did not influence my opinion of this product.

My comments are based on my experiences with the product. I am also a consumer and appreciate reading and giving honest feedback about products.

product_title: LAMY Safari Rollerball Pen, Shiny Black (L319BK)
review_headline: Why spend more for an everyday pen?
review_body:
Years ago I purchased a Safari fountain pen and ballpoint pen. I still have them, and they both look great and function flawlessly.

Now that I'm signing checks and keeping an activity journal at work, I decided to purchase something as an upgrade to the Pilot gel pens (good pens, too) that I use for regular writing tasks.

This Lamy pen is as well-built as the pens I purchased at least a decade ago. It fits my fingers perfectly, and is very balanced - especially with the cap on the end while writing. The ink flows generously, but dries quickly and avoids smudging. I can write for a long time with this pen and not experience any discomfort.

I've spent money on pens costing $50 more than the cost of this Lamy, but I wish I never had assumed higher price meant a better quality pen or a better writing experience. There really isn't anything bad I can mention about this Lamy pen.

product_title: Canon Office and Business MX922 All in One Printer, Wireless and mobile printing
review_headline: but everything went fine - no problems at all
review_body:
I was not looking forward to setting this up for my parents based on some of the other reviews here, but everything went fine - no problems at all. I bet in a lot of cases, PEBCAC (Problem Exists Between Computer and Chair). It was a slow setup however. The printer needed almost half an hour to calibrate itself, and the software took just about as long to install.

Once up and running, we were all completely satisfied with both B&W and color print quality. It seemed on pace to meet its advertised PPM stats. One thing I was NOT impressed by was the warmup time. Once the printer is asleep, it takes a solid 5 minutes to warm back up, regardless of what you want to do. That's no good.

One other nit to note. A big selling point on this printer for me was wireless printing from Android sources. Both of my parents do the majority of their computing on Android tablets (Asus and Samsung). While the ipod app is clean, robust, and easy to use, the Android app is a terrible joke. Dead serious - it looks like DOS Shell, except not as attractive or user friendly (kids, DOS is something we old people used before Windows... and Windows is something we used before Android and iOS). Functionality via the app is EXTREMELY limited, non-self-explanitory, and unreliable. Some jobs had to be requested multiple times because the printer would suddenly become "not found" by the app.

Nits aside, the print quality is high, as is the scan quality. Mom was able to set the fax up herself after I left, so that must have been pretty easy - she's technologically inept. You get a pretty good amount of bang for your buck stuffed into this device. I am deducting one star because Canon has not crossed all their t's and dotted all their i's. Initial setup, and more importantly, wake up needs to be MUCH faster. Android support is just embarrassing. Otherwise, very solid machine.

1. Looks very good while charging

3. Sound is loud and clear

Cons:
1. Functionally the phone is a miss for me as I cannot adjust to the curved speakerpiece. It hurts my shoulders.

I have returned this for the other model KX-PRS120W

product_title: School Smart Electric Heavy-Duty Pencil Sharpener
review_headline: Don't cut it when the hard jobs come.
review_body: I work for the a school and we are preparing for testing this week.  I was given the task of sharpening 600 pencils today.  I used two of these sharpeners and overheated both of them very quickly, admittedly they were elderly machines, but I still ended up using a hand crank sharpener.  Even when they were working they would break of the leads of about 15% of the pencils sharpened, requiring me to sharpen the pencil again.  About half of the pencils ended up with uneven leads, wood down nearly to the tip and only a little pure lead point exposed.  The best pointed ones still did not meet my expectations for a good sharp point that will last through writing more than a sentence or two.

product_title: Lampedia Replacement Lamp for SONY HS50 / HS51 / HS60 / VPL-HS50 / VPL-HS51 / VPL-HS60
review_headline: 18% the life expectancy, much lower price - maybe worth the trade off if you don't worry about replacing it every 6 mo.
review_body: My original bulb ran for not less than 3,100 hours.  (and exploded cracking the inside bulb)  This bulb lasted 558 hours - under 1/5th as long (18% of the life of the other bulb) - Then exploded, so violently that it cracked the glass surrounding the actual bulb part.  It seemed to contain the blast OK though.  This bulb was brighter (slightly) than my old bulb after 3,100 hours (it had said to replace it for the last 2,000 hours of that because of the less than 95% brightness)  This new bulb never had the 'replace bulb' light come on, so it was never considered too dim.  I bought another one of these bulbs, because they cost about 1/5th the price of a 'good bulb' and I could get it quickly.  If you use these, I would recommend keeping a spare on hand, they are cheaper, so you can afford to do that.  Still, I might consider getting a real Sony lamp and then not have to worry about it for 3-5 years!

Be sure to specify where you want it to appear on a page, the top or bottom! I didn't see this option and the default position is the bottom and had to reorder a template so that it appears on top of page. I don't know why the default is for the bottom of the page, don't most of use always put it at the top of the page? It comes in a case, but once I took it out of the case, I was never able to get it back in the case the way it came so the storage case is useless. Otherwise, this embosser is a good product, nice and sturdy and good deal for the money. Practice on paper before you use it on a book page is my recommendation. Company selling this product top notch customer service. If you do have to reorder the right part and send back the wrong one, do not put on the envelope refused so you won't have to pay return shipping. That is mail fraud. Pay the money to ship it back.

product_title: Canon imageCLASS MF8280cw Wireless 4-In-1 Color Laser Multifunction Printer with Scanner, Copier and Fax
review_headline: In the Canon MF8280's world, paper has only one side. If paper has TWO sides in your world, this is the wrong machine for you.
review_body: This might be a decent upgrade from an inkjet (then again, what isn't?), but compared to similar (even 'lesser') laser printers, it's remarkably poor.    It goes through toner like a five year old hitting a stash of pixie sticks (not helped by the fact that the toner cartridges are unusually small -- and expensive, given their capacity).    No duplex scanning, copying, or even printing. Weighs over sixty pounds, and they couldn't even squeeze in a duplex printing option.    If you're upgrading to this from another laser printer simply to get color printing capability, you are making a mistake and selecting the wrong machine.    If you're upgrading to this from any other type of printer for a personal home office, you are selecting an unwieldy beast that does one job reasonably well (faxing: who cares) and three things half as well as a machine that does it properly.    If you're buying this for a professional office of any kind, this is half the machine you want, for twice the toner replacement hassle.    With all that said: as a paperweight, the MF8280 is Top. Notch. Even the flimsiest of receipts will stay put in gale-force winds with this monster sitting on top of them. (As a bonus, if this is all you use the machine for, the toner only runs out about once a month.)    In summation: if you want to *accumulate* paper in a useless, immobile stack and do nothing else with that paper, this is the printer for you. Otherwise, buy something else.

product_title: AT-A-GLANCE Weekly Planner, Collection, Academic Year, 13 Months, July 2015-July 2016, 5.38 x 8.5 Inch Page Size (YP105A-07)
review_headline: Overall I enjoy the quality & functionality of this planner
review_body:
I generally think planners are over priced. And for this particular planner, I paid fourteen bucks with a little hesitation. Although, I would never pay any more than that, I am pleased with the quality and a functionality of this product. It's a good size to carry around anytime, and jot down some notes.The cover feels soft on touch, but seems durable enough to last all year. I found the layout of weekly planner easy for creating a short list of daily to-dos, and the design is non-destructive. The binding coil won't get on the way of writing towards the edge, at least not as much as I initially concerned. I do think it would be better if four consecutive days are in single page instead of keeping it flat open for a week at glance, especially since this is a spiral binding planner.

The paper seems good quality with right thickness, most of the pens I use won't bleed through except for permanent sharpies(see photos). The paper surface is smooth and I would imagine fountain pen would work fine, though I did not have a chance to test it yet.

product_title: Mobo Chair Mount Ergo Keyboard and Mouse Tray System - 2.5-Inch x 12.5-Inch x 7.5-Inch - Black
review_headline: Broken in 6 mths of Use, but I do wish, OFFICE CHAIRS SHOULD BE MADE LIKE THIS!
review_body: UPDATE: 6 mths later the left hand mouse pad/keyboard support has broken at the left hinge.  So VERY disappointing.  I went to the company website & filed a claim but haven't heard back and the support phone number goes NOWHERE  I've lowered my rating because it appears from the comments on here that this is common problem and one that they must be well aware of.  It has solved the problem I had with having to be contorted to work on the PC, but the flimsy nature and non-responsiveness of the company give me pause.  I never put anything heavier than my brand new wireless keyboard on there, and since I'm right handed, the mouse was on the right hand mouse pad so I'm thinking this might be a design flaw on the left hand piece.  I had such HIGH hopes for this, really.  So disappointing.  I wish they made chairs like this!!!  And I wish I had done it 5 yrs ago.  I bought a new Sealy Posturepedic chair with padded arms with a very slight curve.  The Straight Arm attachments worked fine, but the design of the underside of the arms required 2 little wood blocks be cut for each side to support them.  Once we assembled the chair it probably took another hour to figure out how to get the arms secured, but I've been using it now for a month and they're PERFECT!  I cannot explain how wonderful it feels to have the arms & mousepads at the same level and moving with my chair.  I've been using mice since they came out in the 80's and this is the first time I've truly felt like they can be a normal extension of my hand.  Matter of fact, I use one mouse on my left for one computer and one on my right for the other PC.  The mousepad surfaces are supreme too!! (Note, they include different types of attachments for arms in their kit, but the use of wood blocks where needed will make this a much more forgiving and adjustable install.)  The tray is sturdy.  I haven't had the need to use this for a laptop, but I wouldn't have any hesitation, it's the perfect way to setup the desk  When Iget up I simply lift the tray/keboard and put the mice on it and set it on the desk.  VERY easy to get up fast.  The underside of the keyboard tray has these little rubbe grip strips that work perfectly to keep the tray in place so it doesn't slide around.  This whole arrangement has greatly affected a frozen shoulder issue that I had from constantly reaching for keyboard & mice.  I bought a new wireless keyboard & mice for the PC's and they have also facilitated this being a much better work arrangement.  You will absolutely LOVE this!

product_title: Dell Venue Pro 11 Screen Protector, BoxWave® [ClearTouch Anti-Glare (2-Pack)] Anti-Fingerprint Matte Film Skin for Dell Venue Pro 11
review_headline: A decidedly average protector at best.
review_body:
This was not one of the better screen protectors I've ordered; unfortunately my usual brand discontinued the Venue 11 Pro. While it's functional once on, this was particularly hard to get to lay flat without bubbles and was an even worse dust magnet than most. It is also cut so close to the exact size that a very small amount of error when starting puts it off the other side when you get there.

Once on, like many anti-glare protectors, it gives a slightly cloudy appearance (although this is far from unique to this protector. Get clear if that's going to bother you.) The price is right, for a two pack, it was fulllfilled-by-Amazon so I got it quickly, and once on, it seems of at least slightly better than average durability -- the Venue is a machine shared with a toddler, so it needs to be.

Overall, can't really either recommend or say "stay away.

product_title: Universal Tablet stand PAD mount for 7 - 11 inch iPad PC Smartphone Cellphone
review_headline: Solved a mounting problem and is rock steady
review_body:
I received one of these as a review sample and discovered that it was the solution I had been seeking to mount a tablet on my [[ASIN:B007I8207S Stagg MXS-A1 Adjustable Mixer / Keyboard Stand]]. If you use a similar tabletop stand for keyboards you will understand why I love this - and this is the perfect solution. I also tried this on my [[ASIN:B0002F6JH6 On-Stage KS7365EJ Pro Heavy-Duty Folding-Z Keyboard Stand]] and it was a perfect match for that one as well.

The gooseneck is a little on the long side, but can be bent in such a way as to position your tablet at any convenient reading level. In fact, this is perfect as a tabletop stand or counter stand for folks who want to stand while using their tablets. The gooseneck had no problems holding my Samsung Tab 3 10.1 steady and in the position I needed it. Even when the platform (a keyboard stand in this case) was shaken this assembly kept the tablet in position.

Other reviews have exhaustively covered most of the physical attributes so I will not repeat them. I will say that the clamping mechanism on this stand will open to accommodate up to three inch thick counters and table tops. I do recommend that you not exceed 2.75 inches because it's a tight fit on 3.

I am sure there are a lot more uses than what I described, but if you are using a tabletop style keyboard stand and thought you had to rig your own tablet holder - worry no more. This one is an out-of-the-box solution.

product_title: Joy Fish 8 Inch Nylon Cable Ties Wire Ties (Set Of 100PCs,Black)
review_body: I have never written a scathing review until now.  These things are horrible.  Not only are they made in China, they were actually shipped directly to me from there and took about a month to get here.  But that's not necessarily the reason they are bad.  The reason is that they are junk.  In the batch of 200 that I got, many of them break off when trying to snug them up by hand, even before they are tight, and sometimes even before they are snug.  And they don't break off where you are holding it.  They break off at the point where the tie enters the zipper, making the tie too short to be reused.  Being black usually means that they are UV resistant and can be used outdoors in sunlight.  But if the quality of these is so poor to start with, I can only imagine that they will not last very long into the future.  In my future, I will only be buying from stores and brands I have dealt with previously.  And I'm very sure that I will have to be replacing these with those.

product_title: Alfajr Azan Clock
review_headline: Better than any other Azan clock owned in the past. Superb quality, purpose built with excellent features
review_body:
Writing this review on Eid ul-Fitr (7/17/2015). Eid Mubarak to all my brothers and sisters!

Very pleased with the quality and features of this clock and would recommend it to anyone looking for an Azan clock. Compared to other clocks purchased in the past most of which were Chinese made, this is clearly of better quality and a purposely built Azan clock. The features, quality, and sound are far superior to anything else we have owned. Setup was very easy and instructions were clear and easy to follow. Sound quality is excellent, especially coming from a small speaker. Here is the list of pros and cons:

Pros
- Excellent build quality and feels like it was purposely designed to function as an Azan clock
- Sound is excellent and adjustable, loud enough to be heard throughout the house and very clear on loudest setting
- Has all the features you'd want in an Azan clock, from Prayer time offset to Fajr alarm and snooze function plus more
- Five Azan recordings with a "random" setting that plays a different random recording every time
- Batteries are included, and according to other reviews last up to 6-8 months. AC adapter option also available (adapter needs to be purchased separately)

Cons
- None!

This Azan clock by Alfajr is an excellent investment and a must have in every Muslim household. Purposely built in Saudi Arabia with great attention to detail and quality. Looking forward to getting many years of use from this great clock. Highly recommend!

product_title: Phone Power IF-ITVV-CFFY Phone Power Broadband Telephone Service VoIP Phone and Device
review_headline: Excellent Call Quality - Good Customer Service
review_body:
I was pleasantly surprised by how easy this device is to set up and the call quality is excellent. Since my modem has only one Ethernet port, I set up the device using an Ethernet port on the router. It's a very easy set up and the diagrams provided, while not extensive, are enough to get the job done.

I did have one issue with set up. I couldn't get a dial tone for about 20 minutes. I believe this is fairly unusual. At the same time the run light was flashing red. I thought there might be a connection. I called customer service. The first representative didn't know whether there was a connection, or not, but said someone would call back. About ten minutes later, I received a call from another technician. In the meantime, I had tried the phone again and this time had a dial tone and could make a phone call. The second technician told me that the blinking run light probably meant that the device was updating itself. He was very helpful and had me make a call using the device to assure that it was working properly. Customer service was very responsive. I appreciate that.

All of the features of the device work well. My only concern is price. I set up the phone using the DSL we get that from the phone company. I called the company to find out how much I would save if I had DSL only and no land-line phone service. The answer was that I wouldn't save much. They consider their first mission is to be a phone company and therefore would still charge at the same rate if I only had DSL. This makes the device not cost effective, but if it were, I'd seriously consider using it instead of the land-line.

product_title: Carl Angel-5 Pencil Sharpener, Black, Quiet for Office, Home and School
review_body: First, I almost never write reviews on anything, but this sharpener is awesome. I like a sharp point on my pencils for drawing and I have sampled many electric sharpeners and bought an Exacto sharpener. It puts a good point on a pencil, however when a the lead breaks off I have to disassemble the sharpener and take a drill with a fine bit to get it out. Annoying and takes a long time. I saw the reviews on this sharpener and decided to give it a shot. First the weight, it feels solid in the hand. It will sharpen pencils that are pretty short. I use my pencils down to where I can't hold them anymore and stick them in a pencil extender and keep on drawing. When the lead breaks off it's really easy to get it out. It does take some effort to crank the handle. I think it's because the blade is new. I really like this sharpener. It's one of my treasured possessions now.  The only complaint is that the desk clamp is poorly designed I don't know how they could design such a great sharpener and give it clamp which does not work. Too bad. If you like a nice fine point on your pencil you won't be disappointed. Just don't try colored pencils. They are waxed base and get caught in the teeth of the blade. I recommend it.

product_title: Lee Inkless FingerPrint Pad (S03027)
review_body: This finger print pad worked perfect for me. The prints turn out extremely crisp and clear. At first I thought a wanted a strait black ink but this slightly oily, lighter ink really helps show the subtle details of the print. I won't use it often so I think keeping it in a small, tightly sealed ziplock back will help extend the life although the oil constancy of the ink leads me to believe it won't really "dry out". Still just to be safe, bag it. Plus the lid doesn't really have much of a seal and I don't trust the friction plastic locking tab on the lid in my laptop bag. Also clean up is a snap, there is a barley noticeable oily translucent grayish look on your finger before the print. After you press your finger to the paper the majority of it is gone, a quick wipe on a napkin (or your jeans) and any leftover residue is gone.

review_headline: You get 10 credit card and 2 passport protectors with this set
review_body: You get 10 credit card and 2 passport protectors with this set. I like the designs, although I can personally do without the zebra print. I am not sure how long these will last because they are not very thick, but so far they seem to be holding up very well. If your prime use is just for travelling, then they should last a while. This has a very neat feature, which is that it has RFID Technology. Newer credit cards have this little chip in them that thieves can get some kind of machine to scan your card from far away and get your credit card information, technology these days is very scary to me. Keeping your card in these protectors will block the scan and since a lot of thieves target tourists, these are ideal for travel.  I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest, unbiased opinion.

review_body: I just received the shredder today, 3 days after ordering it!  I was concerned that the dimensions of the shredder were a little too deep, but on arrival, noticed the size was not at all too bulky.  In fact, I would have preferred if it were a little taller, in exchange for a little less depth, but that's a quibble.  Before even turning it on, I loved the drawer and the wheels.  I began shredding a pile of accumulated papers almost immediately, and it whizzed right through the stack which contained a few staples, a couple of vinyl envelopes, and some card stock.  The operation was smooth, quiet, and fast.  To get 5 stars, this shredder needs an auto shut-off and a carry handle.  If the bin gets too full, the little shreds spill over and make a mess.  Wish that could be avoided.

product_title: Epson WorkForce WF-2630 All-In-One Wireless Color Printer with Scanner, Copier and Fax
review_headline: it eats ink like a motherf****r
review_body:
This printer works well as a scanner. However, it eats ink like a motherf****r. If you don't use this printer every day, the print nozzle is going to need constant cleaning (the printer has a built in utility), which sucks ink out of the cartridges. If you want a printer that you will be printing things from daily or are only going to use as a scanner, this works great. However, if you are only going to be using the printer occasionally just to be printing pictures or occasional printing of reports/word documents, go with something else. Probably a laser.

Also had quite a few issues with the wireless set-up on this beast.

However, when I contacted Epson Support they were very helpful, and are sending me a new printer for free (shipping too)

review_body:
Bought this for an Acer SL232HL monitor. The mount works, I've found two issues.

-The mount doesn't allow for the HDMI cable, there is barely clearance to fit it at all, as it is the cable is bent at 90 degrees and this will probably degrade the life of the cable. This is the only reason for the 4 star rating.
-The Acer base mounts with only with tension screw. This is not sufficient to fully torque the mount down and the monitor can swivel. You could fabricate a way to stop the rotation, but I found that the extra rotation allows for more custom angles on my wall mount, so it's a welcome oversight.

product_title: Uniden DECT 6.0 D1788 Expansion Phones
review_headline: Phone Won't Registe and how  is how to fix it
review_body: Ok I got hold of UNIDEN Customer support and they walked me right through on how to fix the problem.      First you need to FULLY CHARGE the phone for at least 24 hours in the charger before you attempt to register the phone.    Once the Handset has been charged for 24 hours then take the handset and put it in the BASE UNIT (the base that has the phone line connected to it).  Once you put it in it will start FLASHING - Registering and in about 20 seconds ( 24 to be exact) it will say Registration complete and you are good to go!  The additional handset really worked great!    The KEY is this:  Charge it for 24 hours NOT the 12-15 the booklet tells you.          I ordered this as an additional Handset for the D1760 Phone System a bought about a week ago.  I got it Yesterday and charged it up for 15 hours like I was told and then tried to register it but got the message Registration failed.  I called Uniden support and they had me on hold for 20 minutes  and they I got disconnected. The Uniden support is pretty bad.  I will give it until tomorrow and if it doesn't work I will send it back.  My recommendation is that order ALL THE PHONES you need at the same time so they all come registered and you don't have to go through with this.  I have used Uniden products for years and they are very good so I guess there must be a first time for everything.

product_title: Pop n' Store Decorative Storage Box with Lid
review_body:
As home school parents that also run a business we are in constant need of boxes and storage units. I have not come across Pop n' Store boxes before but I like what I see. The one Amazon offered me to check out is the medium square box 10 5/8 long, 10 5/8 wide and 5 15/16 high. Not sure why they decided on those exact measurements but I'm sure it's just what someone's looking for. These boxes also come in four larger sizes. The ones for documents will come in handy for us.

Construction wise they are pretty solid. A textured vinyl material covers the outside which offers good protection and looks good. The silver protective corners are flat, still offering protection but are mainly for looks. The inside comprises of a matte black cardboard.

The folding design is perfect allowing the entire box to fit in the lid. The bottom of the box has a mesh fabric that keeps the hard bottom insert from falling through.

The box is excellent for storage or using as a fancy gift box. For the quality you receive the price is decent too. The box I received has a crease in the vinyl on the lid but although not welcomed it doesn't detract from the overall box.

Highly recommended

review_headline: 3 coil charger with small form factor, nice!!
review_body:
Wanted a small 3 coil charger that didn't make the back cover of my Nexus 5 feel as if it was being boiled. This one fit the bill. I've only used it for a day or so, so will come back to update. But as of now, I can report that phone placement is forgiving (as it should be with a 3 coil charger) and there are the added niceties of an audible (but not obnoxious beep) from the charger when you place your phone on it (useful for low light situations) and I'm pretty sure there is a low power magnet inside the charger so you get a bit of grip. The back cover of my Nexus 5 was only moderately warm after being placed on the charger while I slept.

*UPDATED Sept 1
Still like this charger, but it's developed a small issue that I haven't been able to figure out. I'll place my phone on top and get the beep that signals that charging has started. Some time later, the charger will start to beep every 3-5 seconds and charging stops. At first I thought that it was a signal that the battery in the phone was fully charged, but that's not the case. I haven't reached out to the vendor yet, will do that shortly. This doesn't happen all the time, but it happens enough that it is becoming annoying.

product_title: Apache AL13 13" Thermal Laminator and 20 Laminator Pouches
review_body:
I absolutely love this laminator! I have wanted for awhile, I seem to always come across things that make me think, "if I had a laminator...!" So I finally decided to get one!
As expected, the options are nearly limitless, and it can be really overwhelming going into a purchase like this! I started reading reviews, comparing prices, looking at various specifications, trying to figure out what would fit my needs. I am a homeschooling mom, so I wanted this to be able to turn ordinary worksheets into reusable, dry erase worksheets! Also for protecting flash cards, and preserving artwork. I knew I wanted a machine that could do different paper sizes, and different thicknesses. The ease of this machine, as well as the 13" length appealed to me, the reviews were very good overall and the price was great!
I must say, after using this machine a few times, I am very pleased with the quality! The laminations come out smooth and even nearly every time! Only twice I have sent the same page through and it came out slightly less than perfect . Both times I had three layers inside the pouch, and I expected it to take a second run through before sealing completely. After the second trip, each was great! I have had no problems at all with it thus far! It laminates at a great speed, when the sheet comes out the other it isn't warped or rounded, no bubbles, no funny seals. So far, I have only used the included sheets and I like them enough to have ordered more.
I can't say it's necessary, as it's the only way I have used the machine, but I use a piece of blank, ordinary card stock underneath that which I am laminating, to be sure of a nice even, flat feed into the machine. It works great to keep the page (or pages) in place inside the laminating sheet as it goes through.
I highly reccomend this laminator! It heats up quickly, stays hot throughout multiple pages, seals cleanly, and only takes up a small amount of space! The extra length is great for normal kid sized art pages (9x12, not the typical 8.5x11, it makes a difference when you least expect it!), and it also takes much smaller projects perfectly (also fed with the card stock underneath to keep it straighter!). Definitely try this laminator if you're looking for something versatile and less costly than some other brands!

product_title: Samsung SL-M2070FW/XAA Wireless Monochrome Printer with Scanner, Copier and Fax
review_body:
This is a great little laser printer for the money. I've only had mine for about 6 months; seems to be doing the job so far. Some people have noted that the toner cartridge it comes with runs out pretty soon after you purchase the unit -- true. Ours ran out about 3 months after we bought it and we used the printer a moderate -to- high amount. You can get away with taking the toner out and shaking it so the toner redistributes. But the little red replace toner light just blinks non stop until you replace the cartridge. That's a little annoying.

For anyone interested in printing acetate/transparency film with this printer: yes you can. The tricky thing is finding the right brand of film. I've found the Highland 701 for Laser Output works well, but that seems to be discontinued or out of stock.

The Apollo Transparency Film for Laser printers does NOT work with this machine. Tried it and it kept jamming in the printer. I think the film is too slick for the machine to grab on to, whereas the Highland Brand had a little tooth to its surface.

If anyone has tried any other transparency film brands successfully please let me know!

product_title: Ohuhu 48-color Colored Pencils/ Drawing Pencils for Sketch/Secret Garden Coloring Book(Not Included)
review_body:
UPDATE: May 27, 2015:
I'm happy to report that the seller Ohuhu stands behind their product. The issues I mentioned in my review of May 21 have been resolved to my satisfaction. I believe fair is fair, and their willingness to remedy the situation means a lot. I have modified my star rating to reflect my satisfaction with both the product (they ARE good pencils) and their customer service.

ORIGINAL REVIEW: May 21, 2015
First, the good news: these are nice quality pencils, not up to Prismacolor standards, but certainly better than most of the lower-priced alternatives. They lay down some good color, can be blended with a blending pencil, and shading "works" like it's supposed to. The actual "brand" is Marco Raffiné -- made in China. Ohuhu may be the manufacturer?

However, there are some issues (you be the judge of whether or not they're "big" issues):

1. My box contains 47 pencils, NOT 48. I have no idea which one is missing, but I counted them 3 times, and there are only 47 in the box.
2. Several colors are duplicated, so you're not getting 47 (or 48 if you're lucky) different colors. In my box, specifically, color #s 501 (white), 502 (cream), 506 (orange), and 505 (golden/orange) all had duplicates.
3. Two of the pencils had obviously been used and sharpened. They were noticeably shorter, and the sharpening pattern was different from what I assume is the "factory" sharpening pattern ("wide" point vs "narrow" point). This set may have been a return at some point, and was placed back in the "sellable" inventory without checking to see if it had been used.

So buyer beware -- based on some of the other reviews, you may luck out and get a full set of 48 pencils with no duplicates. If so, great! The pencils are actually quite good quality and you should get a lot of good use from them.

I'll keep my set "as is," since going through the hassle of returning them just isn't worth it. There are enough colors (43 not counting the duplicates) to make them useful for my purposes. I'd award 2.5 stars if I could; I like the pencils; just not happy with the assortment/quantity.ince going through the hassle of returning them just isn't worth it. There are enough colors (43 not counting the duplicates) to make them useful for my purposes. I'd award 2.5 stars if I could; I like the pencils; just not happy with the assortment/quantity.

product_title: The Lap King Lap Desk - Navy Blue - The Ultimate Lap Desk
review_body: I'm using it right now as I write this review so I definitely will get use out of it. My 15" Macbook Pro kept sliding off the bumper side that you see in the picture. However, upon removing the cushion and flipping the tray over and reattaching the cushion, it actually holds my computer with literally at most a half inch of slide space. This is enough that I don't leave my computer sitting on the Lap King (I have a toddler and a dog and am just too nervous for that). However when it is in my lap this isn't noticeable at all as I'm not typically shifting that intensely.  When laying down on a couch, again, it is useless the way it was designed. With the flat side that has the slight lip around it, it again holds my computer perfectly. This lip is marketed as giving air flow to keep your computer cooler - a feature that I will never utilize as I'd rather keep my computer in one piece given the choice.  The cushion pillow it comes with is comfortable enough on my lap. I wouldn't use it for traveling on an airplane as there are much better neck pillows out there.  My wife has a 13" Macbook and it is a similar story. Only distinction is there is more room for it to slide so it can fall off easier.  The deciding factor when recommending this to a friend: If I need to put my computer down to go handle something quickly it adds an extra step of first removing it from the Lap King and then finding places to put each down. This doesn't sound like a big deal and it can be the difference between containing a spill or needing to clean the carpet. It also means I need to have a place for each of them around my work area... aka my living room.  Bottom line is that the heat and whatever else may be coming off of a laptop wirelessly connected is something that even completely unconscious people are starting to realize doesn't serve. That's why laptops aren't actually even called laptops anymore. It's not safe, nor a good idea to keep them there. The Lap King can be a solution to this. Another more accessible solution is to use any pillow from the couch. If my computer could stay on the Lap King's bumpy side without sliding off and thus have that extra space of air underneath it this would be a no brainer. As it stands, this is slightly better than a pillow in my book.  Update: After using this for over a month now I have come to like it much more and am raising my review from 3 stars to 4. My computer stays sturdily on it. It fell off one time and it was because I put it down on a plate by accident and it slid right off - definitely my fault. I've used this a couple of times in the car as well and I find this to be the biggest difference maker in my life. Also, while I may have couch pillows within reach nearly all the time, I use this far more often than I EVER used a pillow. I also need to say that I received this product in exchange for an honest review.

product_title: YoYoInk CLI42 Parent
review_body:
I had bought this ink a while ago after my standard ink cartridges ran out in the printer. Upon arrival, ink was leaking from the packaging. I used the ink for a bit and quickly replaced them with another off brand ink. This ink was really saturated so I decided to try and buy the yo-yo ink again...

I purchased may 13th 2016, and before I switched out my ink to this one, I made a test print. I then switched out the other ink with the yoyo ink and noticed the colors were much more accurate.

I'm guessing people have an issue with ink spilling still with these and it's probably due to poor packaging. In an effort to save money, yo-yo sends these the ink in a thin box with no padding, and then inserts the box into a mailing envelope with bubble wrap. It's definitely not the best packaging and can easily damage in transit. Luckily, my ink was not damaged this time around but your mileage may vary.

Overall, I recommend this ink to everyone looking for good ink at a good price. If you are a professional, you might want to stick to the original ink, but at 30 bucks, it can be worth a shot to evaluate and help save some money.

review_headline: This product is very good, durable materials
review_body: This product is very good, durable materials.  In fact, this will probably outlive your door.  Alignment prior to drilling holes is crucial, so spend an extra few minutes marking before slapping the pieces in.  Even if you don't get the holes perfect there is some room for error and it will still function properly.  I do not reccoment using the cheap anchors they provided, the magnetic base will simply pull out of the wall (Screws and all) when you pull the door due to the fact that the magnet is very strong, and it also depends on how well the 2 pieces are aligned as to the strength of the magnetism.  As long as the pieces are aligned properly and you use an alternate anchor from a hardware store you should be happy purchasing this item.  I bought 4 and they all work great!

review_body:
These cards are fantastic! They are sentimental yet simple and elegant. A lot of the cards out there are either too cheesy or silly or way too sentimental. The sayings on these cards sums up things you want to say. The red card says "my father gave me the greatest gift anyone could give another person; he believed in me" I know I feel that way about my dad and I'm sure a lot of people feel the same way. The orange cards (with red writing) say "My life is full of wonderful memories of things you have done for me. You are a beautiful person and I love you endlessly" This card could be for a parent, a spouse or anyone who has had a lot of meaning in your life.
Both cards are on a nice heavier stock - thicker than most cards usually are. I like that they are blank on the inside so you can write whatever your heart desires. There is a nice amount of space so you can use both sides and have a long message or use one and just have a basic sentiment or signature.
An added bonus is that the cards were designed and made in the USA.
I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion and review.

product_title: Click 'N Dig! Key Finder. 4 Receivers. Wireless RF Item Locator Remote, Wallet, Keyfinder. (Free Extra Batteries) New Model: E4
review_body: I lose everything..well I don't lose it, I misplace it. I spend way too much time searching frantically for my phone, my keys, my wallet, my mind.  I bought the Click n Dig frankly because the other gadgets in this category were more expensive. My expectations weren't very high due to the low price and I and I was worried it would be difficult to use and clunky attached to my most important things. I should have bought 2 sets! I attached the fobs and disks to the items mentioned activated them by pulling the tabs and heard 4 satisfying beeps.  The only problem I had was the stick ons fell off my phone and tablet when they got warm.  Solved that problem by attaching a Velcro grip for hanging hooks.  Works like it should have come with the box.  I put the receiver in my purse since it's the only thing I dont lose.  The clck n dig paid for itself within the week.  I 'misplaced' my wallet in a busy store while loading groceries and panicked. Then I remembered my secret weapon.  I couldn't remember which button set what off but I'm more than happy to say my wallet chirped like music and I found it behind the counter.  I find the volume just right for me and had no trouble shutting it off.  I did have to put the transmitter in a hard sided case to keep from setting it off with pressure in my purse.  I love this mind saver!  I only went down a star because I had to futz with the stick ons and one of the battery covers popped off.  I taped a piece of the box it came in over the opening  and I'm a happy camper and customer!!

product_title: CPR V202 Call Blocker - Block All Robocalls, Political Calls, Scam Calls, Telemarketing Calls, Unwanted Calls On Landline Phones. Block All Nuisance Calls At The Touch Of A Button Using Caller Id
review_headline: Great call blocker, instructions could be a little clearer
review_body: This appear to be working really well, in that my phone has pretty much gone SILENT! That is, the calls I'm interested in receiving come through but those annoying automated calls are by and large getting completely blocked. I gave it 4 stars instead of 5 because the minimal instruction manual could have been a bit better written. It took me a bit of time to figure out how to program it. I basically have to hold the red button down for 5 seconds to get it into programming mode then enter the codes or numbers to be blocked VERY QUICKLY, otherwise the programming doesn't work. Also, so far the blocked call counter says it's only blocked 8 calls, which is the same number of codes and numbers I've programmed to be blocked. But it must have blocked a lot more calls than that because we used to get multiple robo-calls every day and we're not getting none. Anyways, this unit does pretty much exactly what I wanted it to do and is highly recommended.

product_title: Carl Pencil Sharpener. CC-2000. 5-Points Selector. Manual, Quiet for Office and Home Desks, School Classroom
review_body:
This is an amazing pencil sharpener. Every Artist knows that a sharp pencil is the key between OK and Michelangelo quality. This will make you a Michelangelo.
This is the first crank or electric sharpener that I have ever used in my 70+ years that will put a perfect point on my CarbOthello pastel pencils. They are strong and never break. Odd sized pencils don't work, because there is no size adjustment. Stabilo pencils fit this sharpener perfectly. They are fortunately average sized. Look at your sizes. Conte' or Prismacolor don't work. It has 5 sharpness levels that you can dial to suit the softness/hardness of the lead.

I had to watch a UTube video to understand how to operate it. (Mine didn't come with a "How to manual"). The internet is easier than reading a dull little book when you are anxious to get to work.
I think I'll buy my grown children each one of their own. They will love their Mom even more.

product_title: Pilot FriXion Ball 3 Wood - Brown Body
review_headline: One of my favorite pens - I love the wood grip
review_body:
OK, it's not quite perfect, because I wish the rest of the barrel was metal or wood, and to be honest, it's a little pricey, but it just works -- I fell in love when I saw this online (I was looking at FriXion ball 3 metals), and just love using it - the wood grip is just cool, and I like the color combination (barrel and body, unlike the ball 4 wood models).

We'll see how long the refills last, but so far I'd say they're one of the better writing Frixion refills I've used, with reasonably fine line, good color, and pretty smooth (not as good as a Pilot or Uni 0.4mm gel, but still good)

Update - still loving it. I'd say the refills are the best writing Frixion refills I've used, although the results of course vary with the paper (and still aren't as good as a top gel pen). They haven't run out yet, but I don't use it heavily (think writing quick notes, not essays).

product_title: Pilot FriXion Clicker Retractable Erasable Gel Pens
review_body:
Several months ago Amazon randomly sent this pen to me as a sample along with something that I had ordered. My first thought was "ohhhh sneaky Amazon trying to get me to buy more stuff! You won't get me to!"

I took this pen to work to give it a try. It took me a while to get used to the retractor being on the side but truthfully this is one of the best pens that I have ever used. That is saying a lot for me because I LOVE collecting pens and I very rarely use one until it runs out of ink. I didn't realize the value of an erasable pen until I tried this one out. I have tried others in the past (including another model of FriXion and this one is by far the best. It erases so nicely. It writes nicely. Everything about this thing is great.

I just discovered this morning that my beloved clicker will die soon so here I am to order more and in LOTS of different colors which is CRITICAL for a pen lover.

So kudos to Amazon for knowing I would fall in love with this pen and want more. Sneaky sneaky Amazon.

product_title: V-LIGHT Adjustable Desk Task Lamp, Yellow (EN804Y)
review_body:
What's not to love about this lamp? The V-LIGHT Architect-Style CFL Swing Arm Task lamp is a nice adjustable desk or work table lamp. It's a simple design but it is perfect. As long as it has about an inch or two of solid ledge to attach to, you can attach it horizontally or vertically. No tools required, just but the bracket on the the ledge and tighten the screw-easy peasy! It's a little more difficult to remove, as it stays TIGHT but I like being able to move it to another bench or take to a show if needed. Of course, if you'd like a more secure/permanent placement, you could easily screw this onto the desk/workbench/shelf.

The lamp rotates 360 degrees, which makes it perfect for my workbench when I need more light while sawing metal or I can swing it over to the bench shears when I need to cut something there. Or I can bring it close to the work surface if needed too while setting stones. It folds up a bit to move it out of the way when needed as well. This includes the CFL light bulb and the cord is about 5 ft long.

Overall, its a great addition to my work bench. I have two and will be buying a few more.

product_title: uni-ball Deluxe Rollerball Pens (0.7mm)
review_body: Best Pens ever! I mark up engineering drafts and when I use "other" fine point pens, they ALL bleed into the paper leaving behind an ugly looking line. product_title: Philips Wireless phone/modem jack system PH0900
review_body: I have always been a bit skeptical about running low voltage signals over house wires, but I needed a way to connect my DirectTV box to a phone line to get caller ID, so I decided to give this a try.  The only challenge was deciding where to place the sending unit, beyond that installation as simple as you can get.  The unit worked perfectly, I hear no interference with the phone service or any other electrical device in the house.  For what it worth my phone service is through the cable company.  As for other reviewers, I am not an electrical expert but I suspect if you have a newer house with properly grounded, 3 prong outlets (although this device is only two prong) the unit will probably work well, older homes with different wiring may be less successful.

product_title: Avery Heavy-Duty View Binder
review_body:
This binder is used in a small business where it takes lots of abuse. The women employed by our small hedge fund are quite unruly, and I'm used to our binders splitting and cracking, but this one is holding all of these women quite well. I like the non-stick feature, as it keeps the women from grouping together, and allows me to single them out for individual handling. Many of my other binders have been ruined by makeup transferring to the plastic liner, but this binder has been proven effective against the majority of feminine products on the market.

Using a binder of this quality beats having to replace the cheap ones regularly, which allows me to send the binder buying women home in time to make dinner for their husbands. This is easy to open and an all-around good binder full of women.

product_title: AT-A-GLANCE Weekly Planner, Collection, Academic Year, 13 Months, July 2015-July 2016, 5.38 x 8.5 Inch Page Size (YP105A-07)
review_headline: The paper is good quality, and has plenty of room for writing ...
review_body:
The paper is good quality, and has plenty of room for writing down quick notes. Each day, INCLUDING Saturday and Sunday have a full 1/4 page devoted to them. That means that you get 7 days on a 2-page spread, along with an extra box for notes. Solid. The tabs for the months are on both sides of the divider, meaning that you can see which months have passed, and which ones are coming up, regardless of where in the book you are. At the opening of each month, you have a full month view. In fact, as daily planners go, this one is a king amongst planners. So why the docked star?

The spiral binding makes it difficult to finagle the front and back covers. When I fold the thing flat open on my table, it sits flat gorgeously. When I try to close it back up, the pages go back into configuration no problems. The cover, however, sticks. Pound for pound, this has ALL the features that I could hope for in a daily planner, but opening and closing it is a pain. If it weren't for that one major (it's not a minor annoyance when you're opening and closing the planner multiple times a day) annoyance, this would get 5 out of 5 stars. If it's not enough of an annoyance to you, because you just need one place to archive all your dates, you'll be fine.

BONUS: If you use fountain pens, this will be a good choice for you. I used Noodler's Baystate Blue in a Platinum Preppy on this planner, and it didn't bleed through.

review_headline: if you love your albums -- these are a must!
review_body:
I finally got around to organizing over 400 vinyl albums. These outer sleeves were the perfect finishing touch to my project. I used the Spin Clean System to clean the albums, new poly vinyl inner sleeves, new 12 inch record jackets (for damaged/moldy jackets), and these outer sleeves for each album - all bought through Amazon Prime and all delivered in 2 days. This will give my collection years of protection.

I was very pleased how well they fit. They easily hold a single album or 2 record set. Even my 3 album Wings over American album fit inside without forcing. The only albums that did not fit are the "box" type that have a hinged side with square edges. The London Symphony Orchestra version of the rock opera Tommy comes to mind. Other than that everything is nice and protected

product_title: Brother DCPL2540DW Wireless Compact Laser Printer
review_headline: Great Printer after a bit of troubleshooting!
review_body:
I have had the printer for a couple of weeks and it works great after the issues below were fixed.

This is my first review and I am mainly writing it to provide others with tips on using this printer.

1) Connecting printer to WIFI Network - USE A USB CABLE. it will save you much hassle inputting your SSID and Password into the printer.

2) Updating Firmware - USE A USB CABLE- I tried updating firmware over wifi and it kept getting stuck at 30%. If this happens then go to the printer, click menu> General Setup> Reset, and also force close the firmware update utility on your computer. Connect computer to printer with USB cable and launch the firmware utility again, you should now see the printer on port \\"USB\\" select it and follow on screen instructions, it should take about 5 minutes.

3) Wireless printing doesn't wake printer from \\"deep sleep\\" - Update firmware and update CUPS Drivers, downloadable from the Brothers website. Reboot the printer AND your computer so the driver updates take effect.

Note: After a few emails with brother reps, I realized that \\"auto power off\\" will not work if the printer is connected to the network (wired or wireless) not a deal breaker but something to keep in mind.

product_title: Pilot Dr. Grip Center Of Gravity Ballpoint Retractable Pen, Medium
review_body:
Dr. Grip Center of Gravity pens have been my favorite pen of choice for years. They are very comfortable in your hand and they write so ridiculously smooth that even writing out long reports is no problem with one of these. One refill if you do an average amount of writing each day will last you a couple months at least and the refills are readily available. The only thing I could think of that would make these better would be if they made more colors and a fine tip refill instead of just medium tip.

Keep a very close eye on these pens though... Once people get a chance to try it they have a tendency to walk away if you don't claim it back right away.

product_title: 3M Knob Adjust Keyboard Tray, Standard Platform
review_body: We're not allowed to drill into the desks at our office (We're on a sub-lease w/borrowed desks) so this product was right up my alley. Before I purchased, I saw reviews stating that this product was "not as stable as you think" After installing the product, I understand why someone gave that review, but that doesn't mean you shouldn't buy this tray.  The tray attaches to your desk in two areas; The obvious front clamp that you tighten to fit, and a adhesive w/ hairpin like velcro like connectors at the back of the tray track (this will all make sense once you buy the product.) When I went to collapse my tray under my desk at the end of the day (after I installed it) the back part came loose and my keyboard tray wasn't sturdy any longer. Upon further inspection, I realized that I had dislodged the back part of the tray due to pushing down too hard on it. If the back of the tray was attached via adhesive alone, the product would have been 100% useless. Luckily 3M had foresight into the matter, and installed the hairpin-like "velcro" to steady the track, without ripping off the adhesive.  tl;dr - This product is fairly sturdy, considering it's a product that doesn't utilize screws. As long as you're delicate with how much pressure you put on the keyboard tray, this product works great. This product is great for my situation, and I highly recommend it for anyone else that doesn't want to drill into their desk, but still wants a solid adjustable keyboard tray.
